(25, 'Internship', 'internship', '<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 18pt;"><strong><span class="">Work &amp; Study in the U.S.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span class=""><strong class="">Study for your U.S. Degree while working and earning U.S. wages as EARLY AS YOUR FIRST SEMESTER!</strong></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span class=""><strong class="">Gain U.S. Work Experience and U.S. Degree so you Become a Strong Candidate in the Competitive Global Job Market</strong></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class=""><em class=""><strong>Study</strong>:</em> Students can get employment opportunities (<a class="" href="http://www.htir.co.in/cpt-employment/">Curricular Practical Training</a> , CPT, <a class="" href="http://www.htir.co.in/htir-work-study-in-usa/">internships</a>, work-study, on-campus employment, or co-op opportunities) in the USA for students who want to earn a US degree from an inexpensive yet fully accredited, high quality <a class="" href="http://www.htir.co.in/universities/">university</a>.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class=""><strong class=""><em class="">Work</em></strong><em class="">:</em></span> <span class="">In many of these work and study opportunities, students can work in full time, paid, practical training employment sometimes as early as the first semester of the degree program in order to enhance the educational experience.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong class="">INTERNSHIPS BEGINNING IN SECOND YEAR</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">Off-campus Curricular Practical Training or internships starting after one year of study. This is authorised by SEVIS if Curricular Practical Training (CPT) is offered by the university and is an integral part of the curriculum.</span></p>\r\n<div class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong class="">INTERNSHIPS BEGINNING IN FIRST YEAR</strong></span></div>\r\n<div class="">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Off-campus MANDATORY FIRST YEAR Practical Training Internships: Part-time or Full-Time paid internships as early as the first semester of study. This is authorised by SEVIS only for graduate students at universities where such internship is a mandatory component of the curriculum and is required to begin immediately.</span></div>\r\n<p class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class=""><strong class=""><em class="">Earn</em></strong><em class="">: </em></span><span class="">In many of the work and study opportunities, students earn <a class="" href="http://www.htir.co.in/internship-income/"><strong class="">U.S. wages</strong></a> to use to pay for educational and living expenses.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class=""><strong class=""><em class="">Scholarships:</em></strong></span> <span class="">The schools, and private organisations have scholarships as early as the first semester. We helps you locate and apply for one of the many scholarships available to International Students..</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;"><a class="" href="http://www.htir.co.in/scholarship/"><strong class="">Read more about available scholarships</strong></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class=""><strong class=""><em class="">Student Loans</em></strong></span><span class=""><strong class="">:</strong> </span><span class="">Many of the featured schools, as well as private organisations, have financing available for students without needing a U.S. sponsor. We assists students with locating the financing, as well as co-signing if the need arises.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong class="">Benefits of Applying Through us</strong></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">Paid Employment Opportunities often beginning as early as the first year</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">Scholarships or Tuition Discounts</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">Monthly Tuition Payment Plans or a Student Loan </span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">Affordable Tuition Fees of $3,000 to $5000 to start and about $1,000 per month</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">ESL (English as Second Language) available as needed for accepted students</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">No TOEFL or IELTS required for Admission</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">No GRE or GMAT required for Graduate Applicants</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span class="">Rapid Application and I-20 Processing</span><span class=""><br class="" /> </span></span></li>\r\n<li class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">Free Visa Interview Orientation Course Prepared by a U.S. Lawyer</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong class="">Types of Employment Available</strong></span></p>\r\n<div class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">1) On-campus paid employment: Up to 20 hours per week available for both undergraduate &nbsp; and graduate students, beginning in the first year.</span></div>\r\n<div class="">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">2) Off-campus Curricular Practical Training or internships:Up to 40 hours per week of &nbsp; off-campus paid employment starting after one year of study.This is authorised by&nbsp; SEVIS if Curricular Practical Training(CPT)is offered by the university.</span></div>\r\n<div class="">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">3) Off-campus FIRST YEAR Curricular Practical Training: Paid employment or internships&nbsp; up to 40 hours per week, as early as the first semester of study. This is authorised &nbsp; by SEVIS only for graduate students at universities where such employment is a &nbsp; mandatory component of the curriculum and is required to begin immediately.</span></div>\r\n<div class="">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=""><span class="" style="font-size: 10pt;">4) Off-campus unpaid internships: Employment for training purposes only.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 17, 'Internship', 'Internship', 'Internship', 1, '2016-11-23 19:47:32', 0, 'default-user.png', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0),
