(23, 'University of Southern Queensland (USQ)', 1967, 'Australia', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/University-of-Southern-Queensland-USQ.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/The-University-of-Sydney.jpg', 'Toowoomba, Queensland', '487/521-535 West St, Darling Heights QLD 4350, Australia', '', 'IELTS 6 / TOFEL 80', 'PRIVATE', '9000-10000 AUD', '\n Business & Commerce\n Creative Arts & Media\n Education\n Engineering & Built Environment\n Health & Community\n Humanities & Communication\n Information Technology\n Law and Justice\n Sciences\n English Language\n Pathways Programs\n Professional Development', '', '24,756', '', '', 'ON/OFF CAMPUS', '61 1800 269 500', 'admission@studymetro.com', '', 'spring/fall, summer', NULL, 'AUD$100', 'www.usq.edu.au/\n', 'https://www.facebook.com/usqedu/\n', 'https://twitter.com/usqedu?lang=en\n', 'https://plus.google.com/+UsqEduAu\n', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/university-of-southern-queensland\n', 'https://www.instagram.com/usqedu/?hl=en\n', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o3HrV04YTaM\n', '', '["","","","","","","","","",""]', NULL, 'USQ', 'The University of Southern Queensland (USQ) has forged a reputation as one of Australia''s leading providers of on-campus and online (distance) education programs in Australia. With more than 75 percent of students studying via distance or online, our delivery of external education resources continues to lead the way.', '\nPlans and reports \nEnvironment and sustainability \nHistory of USQ \nHealth and wellbeing \nAccolades \nCulture and values \nAbout USQ\n \nSocial Justice\n\nProviding accessible and equitable educational pathways.\n\n \nMulticulturalism\n\nSupporting USQ''s wide variety of cultural identities, languages, and beliefs.\n\n  \nRacism. It stops with me.\n\nUSQ has a commitment to the eradication of racism.\n \nPlans and reports\n\nOur annual report, strategy and plans for the future.\n\n \nEnvironment and sustainability\n\nWe''re committed to reducing our carbon footprint.\n\n \nHistory of USQ\n\nOur evolution and history over the past 40+ years.\n\n  \nHealth and Wellbeing\n\nCommitment to providing a healthy place of work and study.\n\n \nAccolades\n\nAwards received and given by USQ.\n\n  \nCulture and values\n\nBringing our purpose and values to life. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(24, 'Wentworth Institute,Sydney', 1904, 'Australia', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Wentworth-InstituteSydney.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Wentworth-InstituteSydney.jpg', 'Surry Hills', '302-306 Elizabeth St, Surry Hills NSW 2010, Australia', '', 'IELTS 6 / TOFEL 80', 'PRIVATE', '9000-10000 AUD', 'Vocational Education\nVET Certificate Courses\nVET Diploma Courses\nVET Advanced Diploma\nCourses\nHigher Education\nUndergraduate Programs\nBachelor of Business\nBachelor of Interactive\nMedia\nBachelor of Business\n(Professional Accounting)\nDiploma of Business', '', '', '', '', 'ON/OFF CAMPUS', '61 2 8252 9999', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$30,760/yr', 'spring/fall, summer', NULL, '200', 'www.win.edu.au/\n', 'https://www.facebook.com/WentworthInstitute/\n', 'https://twitter.com/wentworthinst\n', 'https://plus.google.com/+WentworthInstituteofTechnologyBoston\n', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wentworth-institute-sydney\n', 'https://www.instagram.com/wentworthinstitute/\n', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hxlo0fdOggQ\n', '', '["","","","","","","","","",""]', NULL, 'Wentworth Institute,Sydney', 'William Charles Wentworth grew up in Sydney, and returned to England at the age of thirteen where he was educated. He arrived back in New South Wales at the age of twenty in 1815 the year that most people would declare was the beginning of his   ‚Äòlifetime of achievements.‚Äô\n\nWentworth was a landowner and sheep grazier who had an adventurous spirit and a desire to discover new pastures; this led him at the young age of twenty three in 1818 to undertake the first inland exploration in New South Wales, the crossing over the Blue Mountains, west of Sydney. He completed the difficult but successful exploration alongside his fellow explorers Gregory Blaxland and William Lawson.\n\nWentworth returned to England in 1822 and studied at Cambridge University,  studied law and became a Barrister. In the years 1824-1827 he became involved in politics and became a political activist. He wrote a book, which had a big impact on migration in Australia; it referred to the subject of immigration and ‚Äòwhy people should come to live in Australia, rather than America‚Äô. In the same year he argued for freedom of the press and founded Australia''s first newspaper called ‚ÄòThe Australian''. He remained co-owner of the Australian from 1824 until 1827.', 'William Charles Wentworth also played a major part in the Australian political system. He was 64 when he moved to have changes made to the Constitution Bill and this contributed to Australia having responsible government. He also argued for trial by jury and a formal process of appeal, which were laws that hadn‚Äôt previously existed in the Australian penal system.\n\nWilliam Charles Wentworth not only played a huge part in the political landscape of Australia but also became involved in Education. Between the years (1848-1854) he reformed education in New South Wales, he established primary school education in NSW, and most importantly he established the first Colonial University in the British Empire in 1848-49.\n\n \n\nWentworth had a full and adventurous life, he changed lives as well as influencing laws, politics and notably the educational systems in Australia. We hope our students can learn from William Charles Wentworth‚Äôs creativity, adventure, bravery, commitment to education and the pursuit of excellence. We hope that they will fully participate in the quality education that the Wentworth Institute has to offer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
