r the same day by the establishment of Dublin City University.\nThe university is located along the River Shannon, on a 137.5 hectares (340 acres) campus comprising 46 hectares (110 acres) on the north bank and 91.5 hectares (226 acres) on the south bank, 5 km from Limerick city centre. The university has currently in excess of 11,000 full-time undergraduate students [5] and 1,500 part-time students.[citation needed] There are also over 800 research postgraduates and 1,300 taught postgraduate students[citation needed] at the university. The Co-operative Education (commonly called Co-Op) programme allocates all students with an 8-month work placement as part of their degree. This was the first such programmes in the state.\nProfessor Don Barry, a graduate of Yale University, is the current president of the university, having been appointed in 2007.[6]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
