(155, 'Central America Health Science University', NULL, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Central-America-Health-Science-University-logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Central-America-Health-Science-University-Back-ground.jpg', 'Belize City, Belize.', 'Mile 13 1/2 Philip Goldson Highway, Boom Cut Off Rd, Ladyville, Belize', 'The University is chartered by the Government of Belize and is approved by the Ministry of Education in Belize. The Central America Health Sciences University is listed in the World Directory of Medical Schools, published by the World Health Organization (WHO) in Geneva, Switzerland. The University is recognized by the Educational Commission on Foreign Medical Graduates (ECFMG) for students to sit for the USMLE and to facilitate admission into a residency program in the United States. It is also recognized by the General Medical Council (GMC) of the United Kingdom to allow students to sit on the Professional Linguistic Assessment Board (PLAB) and to facilitate admission into a residency program in the United Kingdom.', 'Educational Document \nEnglish proficiency is recomonded \nMCI eligibality Certificate', NULL, NULL, '2 ys study \n2 Yr clinical Reserch', 'Executive dean - Maurice Modavi', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '501 664-4502', NULL, '$ 30 000 - $ 50 000 ', NULL, NULL, '$100', 'http://www.cahsu.edu.bz/contactcahsu.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(156, 'Capital Medical University', 1960, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Capital-Medical-University-logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Capital-Medical-University-back-ground.jpg', 'China, Beijing, Fengtai', NULL, '14 hospitals in China, 11 worldwide', 'Filled application form of CCMU 2- Passport (First 4 pages and visa Scan, if have any other country visa) 3- Matriculation and FCS or O-Level & A-Level or equivalent to 12th grade education mark sheets and certificates. 4- Signed fees contract  5- Bank statement if required  6- Affidavit of financial sport from guardians, if required  \nPlease scan following documents and name the files according to document type. Send to ccmuadmission@yahoo.com \nNote: \n1. Send complete documents in one email.  2. If your admission is accepted, you will receive Pre-admission letter in 3 working days after submission of the documents. 3. Pre-admission letter will not be issued, if the documents are not complete. 4. Send your complete postal address with contact person name, postal code and contact number along with the documents.  5. Within 30 days you will receive original admission letter and JW202 from University.  6. After getting visa from embassy, send us visa scan and air ticket scan 1 week before your travel. 7. University will give you only one week‚Äôs time for the payment of fees after arrival.  \nStudent Dropout case:  \n1- Please send confirm student documents only.  2- In following cases university will charge money from partners:  \na. If student is dropped after issuing JW202 and he/she doesn‚Äôt report to the university, partner will be charged 300 USD as JW202 fees.  b. If student leaves university within 4 days after arrival, university will charge 950 USD as JW202 fees, dorm deposit and bedding.  c. If the student leaves university after a week, university will charge complete 1st year fees. ', ' Public', NULL, '2 ys study \n2 Yr clinical Reserch', ' Professor Lu Zhaofeng', '26,000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '86 10 8391 1000', NULL, 'RMB 250000 - RMB 60000', 'Oct , Jan ', NULL, '$100', 'www.ccmu.edu.cn', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Capital University of Medical Sciences (S: ??????, T: ??????), also known as CUMS, CCMU or CMU, is a university in Beijing, China, which was originally called Beijing Second Medical College (???????).\nCapital Medical University (CMU) was founded in 1960, with the original name of Beijing Second Medical College (???????). It ranks among the top academic medical institutions in China and is considered as one of the key municipal universities in Beijing. The founding President, Professor Wu Jieping, was a world-renowned urologist, member of both the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of Engineering. The current President is Professor Lu Zhaofeng.\nCMU consists of 10 Schools, 14 affiliated hospitals and 1 teaching institution. The university and the affiliated hospitals have a staff of about 20,000. Among the staff, there are 6 members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences or the Chinese Academy of Engineering, over 1,000 professors, and over 2,000 associate professors. The university has over 9,000 enrolled students. CMU provides a wide range of educational programs for Doctorates, Masters, Bachelors and certificates.\nThe faculty physicians at CMU train annually several thousands of clinical residents and fellows. Also, the faculty members also provide continuous medical education to physicians and other health professionals through seminars, teaching rounds, and tutorials on and off campus. Over the years, the university has graduated a large number of academic leaders and general practitioners for Beijing and the whole country.\nCMU is a well known academic institution for its strong competence in the scientific research. It hosts many national and municipal key disciplines, laboratories and some exchange stations for post-doctoral research. High-caliber national and municipal research and training centers and institutes are founded here, covering a wide range of fields including General Practitioner Training, Clinical Medicine, Basic Medicine, Neurosciences, Ophthalmology, Geriatrics, Urology, Cardiology, Pain Medicine, Toxicology, Biomedical Engineering, Traditional Chinese Medicine, Reproduction, Health Policy and so on. We have achieved national and international recognitions in many areas such as Neurobiology, Cytobiology, Immunology, Medical Iconography, Neurology, Neurosurgery, Cardiology, Cardio-vascular Surgery, Kidney Transplantation, Respiratory Disease, Digestive Medicine, Oral-Maxillofacial Surgery, Ophthalmology, Otolaryngology and Pediatric Hematology, among others.\nCMU provides excellent international exchange programs. It has partnerships and agreements with many universities and institutions with more than 20 countries and regions, supporting activities such as faculty and student exchange programs, joint education and joint research projects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(157, 'Jiangxi University of Traditional Chinese Medicine (JXUTCM) is ', 1959, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Jiangxi-University-of-Traditional-Chinese-Medicine-JXUTCM-logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Jiangxi-University-of-Traditional-Chinese-Medicine-JXUTCM-Back-ground.jpg', ' Jiangxi, China', '818 Xingwan Ave, Wanli, Nanchang, Jiangxi, China', '? 1st Affiliated Hospital\n? 2nd Affiliated Hospital\n? Recognized by World Health Organization (WHO),\n? Recognized by America Educational Commission for Foreign Medical Graduates (ECFMG),\n? Largest Laboratory in China,\n? High Cultural Exchange between over 600 Students,\n? High Quality Teaching by Teachers from India, USA, China, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Nepal,\n? More than 80% of International Students pass Local Licensing Examination at one sitting,\n? Recognized by PMDC, MCI, USMLE, HPCSA, SCHS ETC\n', '1 Fill in the Application Form\n2 Scan the data page of your international passport\n3 Scan High school results\n4 Attach No. 1,2,3,4 in one Mail \n5 Subject of Mail should be Intended Program of Study and Agency Name\n6 Application will be processed and evaluated by the admissions department\n7 If accepted, Admission Confirmation Notice will be sent to you\n8 If required, student should pay application feesEducational Document \nEnglish proficiency is recomonded \nMCI eligibality Certificate\n', ' Public', NULL, '? General Medicine & Surgery (MBBS)\n? One Year Foundation Program\n', 'Prof. Fu Ke Gang', '19000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '86 791 8711 9528', NULL, '$ 30 000 - $ 60 000 ', 'Oct , Jan ', NULL, '$100', ' jxtcmi.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Founded in 1959, the new campus of Jiangxi University of Traditional Chinese Medicine (JXUTCM) is located at the foot of scenic Meiling Mountain range on the western outskirts of the capital, Nanchang City. Since its foundation, the school has been dedicated to the education of students who possess practical and innovative talents. The university‚Äôs academic approach has shown advantages in terms of the schooling paradigm in which the education of Medicine (MBBS) is coordinated with the development of multiple disciplines and demonstrates the unique integration of Medicine, and Clinical research. And in this way the University is made a hub for medical education, therapeutic care and scientific research in Jiangxi Province.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
