lly required to present the following documents:\nd.a)  The copies of the qualification document acquired as a result of enrolment through the Procedure of Enrolment without taking the Unified National Examination ‚Äì Diploma and Diploma Supplement; \nd.b) An act of the head of the higher education institution, certifying the enrolment of the applicant concerned for the first cycle of higher education at a higher education institution through the Procedure of Enrolment without taking the Unified National Examination;\ne) A copy of the document certifying military registration (only for Georgian nationals); \nf) A photo (3X4); \ng) The document certifying the payment of the tuition fee; \nh) The applicants for the enrollment for an English-language program without taking the Unified National Examination shall be additionally required to present one of the language proficiency documents (if there is such), envisaged by Rules for Determination English Language Proficiency;\ni) One of the following documents certifying the stay in a foreign country for two or more years (for foreign nationals, stateless persons or Georgian nationals, who acquired secondary of equivalent thereto education in a foreign country): \nh.a) A document, certifying the registration in a foreign country; \nh.b) A consulate registration document; \nh.c) Any other document, certifying the stay of the applicant in the foreign country in accordance with the law in force of the concerned\n\n\nPreconditions for the Enrolment for a Doctoral Program\na) A completed electronic application form;\nb) A copy of an ID Card (for foreign nationals ‚Äì a copy of every page of the passport/nationality identification document, for stateless persons ‚Äì a copy of a residence certificate); \nc) A qualification document (Master‚Äôs Diploma or equalized thereto qualification document);\nd) A photo (3X4); \ne) The document certifying the payment of the tuition fee; \nf) An international certificate certifying, at least