(160, 'PREMIER HOPKINS UNIVERSITY School of Medicine', NULL, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PREMIER-HOPKINS-UNIVERSITY-School-of-Medicine-Logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PREMIER-HOPKINS-UNIVERSITY-School-of-Medicine-Back-ground.jpg', 'Carabian Ilands ', 'No- 01 , Beausejour Road, North Entrance, Gros Islet, St. Lucia TEL: +1-758-520-0594, +1-758-450-0140/130,          +1-758-488-0322 Email id: info@ph-edu.org URL - www.ph-edu.org\n7610 Carroll Avenue, Suite 360, Takoma Park, MD 20912 United States Inf', 'United States of America \nRecognized & Listed with ECFMG USA (Education Commission for Foreign Medical Graduate US Licensure)\nApproved and Listed FAIMER‚Äôs IMED\nAffiliations with ACGME Teaching Hospitals in USA \nGovernment of St.Lucia \nRecognized and approved by Ministry of Health, The Government of St. Lucia \nApproved and Listed for Canadian Licensing process\nMedical Council of Canada\nRecognized and Listed with World Health Organization - Avicenna Directory (WHO- Avicenna Directory)\nMedical Council of India (To appear for the MCI screening test)', ' Grade 10 +2 /A ''Level- Mathematics, English, Biology, Chemistry, Physics with a B average or 60% ? Transfer Students are accepted from all IMED institutions (with a 3.2 GPA) ? 90 college credit hours in science for admission into the Doctor of Medicine program is strongly recommended with the following courses: ? 2 Semesters of General and/or Inorganic chemistry with lab ? 2 semesters of Organic Chemistry with Lab ? 2 semesters of Biology or Zoology ? 1 semester of English ? 1 Semester of Statistics or Calculus\n', NULL, NULL, 'NRMP\nMD - DOCTOR OF MEDICINE\nCLINICAL AFFILIATIONS.PH Centre for Medical Science (PH-CMS)', 'Dean Dr. John Klir ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'www.ph-edu.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Innovation is the 