(162, 'CENTER FOR AMERICAN EDUCATION at TEXILA AMERICAN UNIVERSITY', NULL, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CENTER-FOR-AMERICAN-EDUCATION-at-TEXILA-AMERICAN-UNIVERSITY-Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CENTER-FOR-AMERICAN-EDUCATION-at-TEXILA-AMERICAN-UNIVERSITY-Back-ground.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Texila American University ‚Äì Center for American Education (TAU - CAE) & Broward College (BC) together offer a 2-year AA (Associate of Arts) program, which provides a pathway for transfer to most colleges and universities in USA, Canada, UK, Lebanon, UAE, Egypt and Japan.  \nAdvantages of TAU-CAE & BC Program  \nSince the duration of an American Degree is 4 years you can start the degree program right after your O‚ÄôLevels. So by the time you are 19 or 20 years old you could have an American Bachelors degree in your hand, while your colleagues may still be struggling to enter a local university.  \nThe TAU-CAE offers 145 subjects at the degree level. So that students can complete half of almost any degree in Guyana - South America, before transferring to the United States and elsewhere to complete the remaining 2 years.  \nStudents are not restricted to transferring only to USA. After completing 2 years of study (61 Credits) at TAUCAE students can also transfer to other countries such as USA, Canada, UK, Lebanon, UAE, Egypt and Japan.  \nOver 2000 students completing this program at Broward College centers around the world have transferred to foreign universities mainly in the U.S. in fields including Pre-Medicine / Engineering / Business Studies / Computer Science / Psychology / Hospitality Management etc.  \nTexila American University & Broward College  \nTexila American University is located in, Georgetown, Guyana ‚Äì South America and currently collaborates with Broward College - USA. Established in 1959 and located in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, Broward College is one of 28 public state colleges in the state of Florida, and serves over 65,000 students.    \nBroward College in Florida offers wide variety of programs including the four-year bachelor‚Äôs degrees ranging from Health Sciences to Business leading to different career opportunities in Allied Health, Business, Information Technology  \nThe intensive English Language Studies Program can prepare students whose first language is not English. TAU also offers a 8 weeks English training program for academic purposes to help Students who have not done their schooling in English or did not pass their TOEFL or IELTS.  \nTexila American University also offers full-time programs in Doctor of Medicine (MD), Doctor of Dental Surgery & Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) Programs on its campus located in Georgetown, Guyana ‚Äì South America.   ', 'Texila American University ‚Äì Center for American Education (TAU - CAE) & Broward College (BC) togeth', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Broward College (BC) was established in 1959. It caters to over 65,000 full time and part-time students from all over the USA and other countries. BC offers academic as well as technical and occupational programs. Broward College is well-recognized for its dedication to international education programs. As such, BC has established formal linkages with several American college programs overseas. Currently, official BC relationships are maintained with the following institutions:  \n1. Texila American University (Guyana ‚Äì South America)  2. Broward College Center for American Education (BCAE) Guayaquil (Ecuador) 3. American College of Higher Education (Sri Lanka) 4. Center for American Education (Singapore) 5. Center for International Education ‚Äì National Management School (CIE-NMS) (India) 6. South Ocean College, Wuxi (China) 7. Institute for American Education ‚Äì Vietnamese American Training College (IAE ‚Äì VATC) (Vietnam) 8. Center for American Education at the Universidad San Ignacio de Loyola (CAE ‚Äì USIL) (Peru)  \nBroward College is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools‚Äô Commission on Colleges to award Associate‚Äôs and Bachelor‚Äôs degrees. Texila American University is not accredited by the Commission on Colleges and the accreditation of Broward College does not extend to or include Texila American University or its students.  Although Broward College accepts certain course work in transfer toward a credential from Texila American University, or collaborates in other ways for generation of course credits or program credentials, other colleges and universities may or may not accept this work in transfer, even if it appears on a transcript from Broward College. This decision is made by the institution subsequently considering the possibility of accepting such credits.  \nBroward College will accept credits in transfer earned by students at Texila American University toward the Associate of Arts degree.  To receive a degree from Broward College, at least 25% of the coursework must be completed at a Broward College location, which includes SACS-approved international centers', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
