(175, 'NTEC', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Lantern_Ntec_Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/ntec-1.jpg', ' Auckland  New Zealand', 'Hobson St, Auckland 1010, New Zealand', NULL, '6.5 overall with all bands 6 or higher', 'Public', '$10,000', 'http://ntec.ac.nz/courses/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '64 9-555 5400', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$22,000', '$150', NULL, NULL, 'http://ntec.ac.nz/', 'https://www.facebook.com/NtecTertiaryGroup/', 'https://twitter.com/', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/national-technology-institute-new-zealand', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRCMA9d3Jf1zb9Ure4kP6_A', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'NTEC', 'Ntec commenced operations in New Zealand in 2004 with the registration of CIB as a Private Tertiary Establishment (PTE). From its humble beginnings the founders have grown Ntec into one of the largest private tertiary providers in the country, with campuses in Auckland, Christchurch, Hawke‚Äôs Bay and Tauranga.\n\nNtec recently became part of Aspire2 Group Limited, which has 29 education and training locations throughout New Zealand, and over 7000 international students from more than 30 countries enrolled across 130 programmes.', 'Ntec prepares students for careers in accounting, business, computing, cookery, hospitality, and health services, and offers a wide selection of English courses, including general, business, academic, IELTS and TESOL.\n\nStudents have the option of completing short-term English and hospitality courses, one and two year diploma programmes, and one-year top-up programmes to the University of Northampton‚Äôs MBA and BA (Hons) Business and Management degrees.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(176, 'NZALI', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/NZALI1.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/NZALI.jpg', ' Auckland , New Zealand', '12 Huron St, Takapuna, Auckland 0622, New Zealand', NULL, '6.5 overall with all bands 6 or higher', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Diploma in Business Management (Level 7), with specialisations in Health Services and Financial Planning', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', '$21,300', '$150', NULL, NULL, 'http://www.nzali.ac.nz/', 'https://www.facebook.com/nzali.ac.nz', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'NZALI', 'At NZALI we provide high quality tertiary courses to New Zealand and international students. Our courses lead to qualifications that are industry-relevant and market-responsive. Our courses are designed and delivered to meet the needs of our students.\n\nOur business management course is one of the most comprehensive in New Zealand, and has been specifically developed to ensure relevance in today‚Äôs international workplace. We provide internships with industry that are linked to our qualifications. We assist our students to set career goals that are relevant to where they want to go in life.\n\nOur mission is to provide high quality tertiary courses to New Zealand and international students that lead to qualifications that are industry-relevant and market-responsive.\n\nOur lecturers are well qualified, and have experience in their fields of study. They take a very personal interest in seeing their students succeed, and are available to assist students as needed (for example with assistance through difficult phases of study). Our class sizes are small, and our courses are interactive and engaging, ensuring that no student is left behind. Our campus environment and service are set up to ensure our students are prepared for success the moment they start their study pathway with us.', 'BENEFITS OF STUDYING AT NZALI\nComplimentary airport pickup on arrival\nMobile SIM card (issued during Orientation Week)\nTwo weeks fully-catered accommodation on arrival (if required)\nSmall lecture and tutorial class sizes (approx. 30 students maximum)\nIndustry-relevant lectures and tutorials\nPersonal attention, made possible by small class sizes\nHealth Services internships offsite, and practical Financial Planning training from a qualified New Zealand financial planner onsite\nCampus located in a very pleasant seaside suburb of Auckland, very close to public transport and the central business district, and about 500m from the beach.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(177, 'NZIBT', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/NZBIT.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/NZBIT-3.png', 'Christchurch , NZ', 'Christchurch 7647, NZ', NULL, '6.5 overall with all bands 6 or higher', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Graduate Diploma in Business ‚Äì Level 7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '64277888117,', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$19,000', '$150', NULL, NULL, 'http://www.nzibt.ac.nz/', 'https://www.facebook.com/nzibtcollege/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'NZIBT', 'Philosophy:\nNZIBT believes in the personal transformational power of education, its role in creating a productive society, and its ability to make a difference in the quality of life.\n\nStrategy One ‚Äì Quality Provision\n1. NZIBT seeks to be a quality, NZQA category one, private training provider teaching applied vocational programmes of study from Level 4 ‚Äì Level 7 on the New Zealand \n    Qualifications Framework\n\n2. NZIBT will select staff, students, agents and partners that align with its strategy of quality provision.\n\n\nStrategy Two ‚Äì Public ‚Äì Private Partnership\n1. NZIBT will partner with high quality, NZ Government owned public providers for programme content and delivery site (unique Public, Private Partnership model)\n\n2. NZIBT will partner with national organisations (INZ, NZQA, ENZ)and locally with the CDC, Chamber of Commerce and the community to ensure that multiple partnership \n    deliverables are being achieved.\n', 'Strategy Three ‚Äì Vocational Education (Industry Integration)\n1. NZIBT will use the best of applied vocational education pedagogy including (but not limited to) problem based, group project, simulation, and critical thinking application \n    to maximize the employability of each student;\n\n2. NZIBT will safely involve students in workplace learning, placement, internships and projects, enhancing the student theory application, cultural integration and vocational\n    outcomes; \n\n\nStrategy Four ‚Äì Employment Outcomes\n1. NZIBT will employ research active, suitably qualified and teaching experienced lecturing staff with national and international credibility.\n\n2. NZIBT will explicitly connect the programme of study offering to the local, national and global workforce labour market needs (especially NZs long term skill shortage \n    outcomes; list)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
