(187, 'International College of New Zealand', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/International-College-of-New-Zealand-Logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/International-College-of-New-Zealand-Back-ground.jpg', NULL, '1021, 145 New N Rd, Eden Terrace, Auckland 1021, New Zealand', NULL, 'Age Criterion: No less than 18\nEnglish Language\nCriterion: An International student needs to show English competency according to one of the following requirements as listed on the NZQA website.\nIELTS score of 5.5 with no band score lower than 5\n(or)\nHave successfully completed a NZQA Qualification at Level 4 and above at a NZQA recognised education provider.\nAcademic Criterion: NCEA Level 2 or completion of Year 12 or form 6 or its equivalent in the student‚Äôs home country\nInsurance: By Law students are required to have current travel and medical insurance covering the period of enrolment.\nImmigration: Student enrolled at ICNZ will not be considered regular bonafide students and will not have the access to the privileges of the college and resources until the time they submit an approved student visa/permit stating legal eligibility to study National Diploma in Business Level 5 at the International College of New Zealand.', 'Private Training Establishment', 'NZ $ 5000 ', 'The National diploma in business NZQA level 5; is designed to be completed in modules. Each module is Nine Weeks long with an average of 20 hours class work. The classroom work is enhanced by Self Directed Learning (SDL) away from the class. This can be done at home or at a Library or any other suitable place of choice & convenience. The tutors are available to help you plan your SDL, but full student commitment is needed in order to attain the required competency levels. Subjects\n‚Ä¢ Contract Law ‚Ä¢ Health and Safety Management\n‚Ä¢ Financial Skills ‚Ä¢ Human Resource Management \n‚Ä¢ Business Administration ‚Ä¢ Business Operations & Development\n‚Ä¢ Strategic Management ‚Ä¢ Small Business Marketing\n‚Ä¢ Business Information Processing ‚Ä¢ Business Communication\n‚Ä¢ People Development and Coordination\n\nThe National diploma in business NZQA level 6; is designed to be completed in terms. Each term is Ten Weeks long with an average of 20 hours class work.There will be a requirement of additional hours for Self Directed Learning (SDL) away from the class. This can be done at home or at a Library or any other suitable place of choice & convenience. The tutors are available to help you plan your SDL, but full student commitment is needed in order to attain the required competency levels.Subjects\n‚Ä¢ Strategic Management ‚Ä¢ Small Business and Financial Management\n‚Ä¢ Human Resources Management ‚Ä¢ Contract Law\n‚Ä¢ Marketing ‚Ä¢ Franchising\n‚Ä¢ Organization & Management ‚Ä¢ Change Management\n\nThe National diploma in business NZQA level 6; is designed to be completed in terms. Each term is Ten Weeks long with an average of 20 hours class work.There will be a requirement of additional hours for Self Directed Learning (SDL) away from the class. This can be done at home or at a Library or any other suitable place of choice & convenience. The tutors are available to help you plan your SDL, but full student commitment is needed in order to attain the required competency levels.Subjects\n‚Ä¢ Strategic Management ‚Ä¢ Small Business and Financial Management\n‚Ä¢ Human Resources Management ‚Ä¢ Contract Law\n‚Ä¢ Marketing ‚Ä¢ Franchising\n‚Ä¢ Organization & Management ‚Ä¢ Change Management', NULL, 'NZ $  16,980', NULL, NULL, NULL, '64 9-369 1698', NULL, NULL, 'January, April, July, September', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
