(189, 'Le Cordon Bleu New Zealand', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Le-Cordon-Bleu-New-Zealand-logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Le-Cordon-Bleu-New-Zealand-back-ground.jpg', NULL, '52 Cuba St, Te Aro, Wellington 6011, New Zealand', NULL, 'IELTS 5.0 Basic Cuisine/P√¢tisserieIELTS \n5.5 Intermediate and Superior Cuisine/P√¢tisserie\n16 years old (no upper age limit)', NULL, 'NZ $ 5000 ', 'Cuisine\nMaster basic to advanced culinary techniques that apply to any style of cuisine. Explore French culinary traditions, global cuisines and current trends.\n\nVIEW THE PROGRAMMES\nPastry & Confectionery\nDiscover the art of P√¢tisserie. Courses range from specialized ateliers, basic through advanced levels of pastry and confectionary craft making, plated and boutique style desserts, world delicacies and precise decorating techniques.\n\nVIEW THE PROGRAMMES\nHotel, Restaurant & Culinary Management\nFrom running your own Hotel or Resort, Restaurant, Caf√© or Boutique business, our diploma and degree programmes instill operational, supervisory and management knowledge, skills and application in the hospitality and food industries.\n\nVIEW THE PROGRAMMES\nGourmet & Short Courses\nFor beginners, gourmet enthusiasts or those wanting to be the best house party host, a wide range of courses have been designed to satisfy the time and budget conscious. A great way to experience first-hand the world of Le Cordon Bleu.\n\nVIEW THE PROGRAMMES\nContinuing Education & Professional Development\nA range of culinary and higher education programmes are offered to expand one‚Äôs knowledge, create opportunities, advance careers or take them in new directions, enhance skills, and encourage new ways of thinking and understanding.', NULL, 'NZD $66,625', NULL, NULL, NULL, '64 4-472 9800', NULL, NULL, 'January, April, July, September', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=27&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjx8N6LuOHOAhXCOY8KHd4lAlkQ9zAIxgEwGg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FLeCordonBleuNZ&usg=AFQjCNFQpZGcJ8Dk26F_rWvKH2r4k3LdxA&sig2=hAhZN8HEB3EwhKQ0OdAEBw&bv', 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=27&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjx8N6LuOHOAhXCOY8KHd4lAlkQ9zAIyAEwGg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2Flcbnewzealand&usg=AFQjCNHNXYHedS3iR0vij500TYDusWS_fA&sig2=e9MF4JYNUDpYlC5HJDhYNw&bvm=', 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=27&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjx8N6LuOHOAhXCOY8KHd4lAlkQ9zAIygEwGg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fplus.google.com%2F%2BLeCordonBleuNewZealandWellington&usg=AFQjCNE0i_6Tb4-eTmmI9xdZmyiJldoeMg&sig2=hVtyK', 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=27&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjx8N6LuOHOAhXCOY8KHd4lAlkQ9zAIzAEwGg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Flcbnewzealand&usg=AFQjCNEQpumIOl5OpUKEQFfuJnOplATJWQ&sig2=hAhK5-ONGtTrINkSRPCQ0A&bv', NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Take the first steps towards realising your ambitions at our boutique international flagship institute in the heart of Wellington New Zealand, where you will be inspired to develop your passion for culinary arts and hospitality management under the direction of our master chefs and lecturers. Our master chefs are both classically trained and qualified teachers, whilst our lecturers contribute a wealth of knowledge gained through years of experience in both education and the hospitality industry.\n\nOur building features state-of-the-art facilities to provide you with the latest and most innovative opportunities in culinary and hospitality education.\n\nWe source local produce and ingredients for use during practical sessions and demonstration, and constantly review our suppliers to ensure you receive the highest quality ingredients. By supplying our students with specialist items, you learn to develop you senses and techniques with premium ingredients to prepare for the professional environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(190, 'New Zealand National College ', NULL, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/New-Zealand-National-College-Logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/New-Zealand-National-College-back-ground.jpg', NULL, '238-242 Queen St, Auckland 1010, New Zealand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'NATIONAL DIPLOMA IN BUSINESS LEVEL 5 --- PROGRAMME OVERVIEW\nCourse : National Diploma in Business\nType : Diploma\nLevel : 5\nNQF Credits : 125\n\nThe National Diploma in Business Level 5 aims to provide learners who hold, or aspire to hold, positions which involve low level management and leadership of a team or business unit or other business related roles with a single focus of technical business competence and skills. The qualification is intended both for people 18 years of age or over, domestic and international, who are seeking recognition of current competence for existing knowledge and skills they use in their work, and for people acquiring skills and knowledge in a range of education settings. The programme exposes the learners to a range of business topics, enabling them to make informed choices about specializations at higher levels should they wish to further progress their studies in Business.\n\nOn completion of the qualification, graduates will be able to undertake a range of business activities and specific roles involving management and leadership of a team or business unit with a single focus in both domestic and international locations. The qualification can lead to study at the diploma level 6 or directly into the workforce.\n\nUpon completion of the programme, graduates will have a wide range of career opportunities in business, including entry and mid?level management or marketing roles in all business sectors. This qualification may lead to National Diploma in Business (Level 6) [Ref: 1499] and/or to other qualifications that more specifically reflect industry specialisations.\n\n\n\nNew Zealand National College\nNational Diploma in Business Level 6\n\n\nNATIONAL DIPLOMA IN BUSINESS LEVEL 6 --- PROGRAMME OVERVIEW\nCourse : National Diploma in Business\nType : Diploma\nLevel : 6\nNQF Credits : 122\n\nThe National Diploma in Business Level 6 aims to provide learners who hold, or aspire to hold, positions which involve low level management and leadership of a team or business unit or other business related roles with a single focus of technical business competence and skills. The course will develop versatile and adaptable graduates that are well equipped to commence a business career or apply for further study to a higher diploma on degree qualification. The qualification is intended both for people 18 years of age or over, domestic and international, who are seeking recognition of current competence for existing knowledge and skills they use in their work, and for people acquiring skills and knowledge in a range of education settings. The programme exposes the learners to a range of business topics, enabling them to make informed choices about specializations at higher levels should they wish to further progress their studies in Business.\n\nPeople who have achieved the National Diploma in Business L6 qualification will have a solid grounding in Business functions as well as a specific level of understanding of the functions of Business related concepts of business related management and leadership activities. Graduates are able to work in areas of some speciality with some technical complexity in a range of business activities and specific roles at a high level in all sectors of business and industry, in both domestic and international locations, including manufacturers, market research companies, international marketing and sales, cultural relations, educational institutions, retailers, brokerage houses, banks and other financial institutions, international business consulting firms, and other large and small entrepreneurial businesses.\n\nUpon completion of the programme, graduates will have a wide range of career opportunities in business, including entry and mid?level management or marketing roles in all business sectors. This qualification may lead to Diploma in Business (Level 7) and/or to other qualifications that more specifically reflect industry specialisations.\n\n\nNational Certificate of Educational Achievement (NCEA)\n\n\n\nInternal practice test reading\n\nInternal practice test writing\n \n\nCertificate in General English (Levels 1-4) \n\nDuration: 12 - 48 weeks \n\nThe English programme is specially designed for students of English as other language (ESOL). The four main levels are: Elementary, Intermediate, Pre-Intermediate and Upper-Intermediate  Students will be assigned their entry level according to their placement test performance.\n\nIELTS Intensive Preparation (Level 4) \n\nDuration: 12 - 48 weeks \n\nThe IELTS Preparation Course is specially designed for students who wish to further their education in universities or any institutions of higher learning. The design focuses on the learning of the skills and strategies that will be needed to meet the challenges of the IELTS examination. The course is aimed at helping students work towards obtaining a score in IELTS examination accepted by institutions of higher learning in English-speaking countries.\n\nCertificate in Teaching English to Speakers of Other Languages (TESOL, Level 4)\n\nDuration: 20 weeks (including 2 week term breaks)\n\nThis TESOL programme is to prepare individuals in the theories, methods and techniques of developing, implementing and evaluating organised learning activities thus enabling them to teach English to speakers of other languages. At the end of the course students will know how to find jobs and work/live overseas, and will have the entire range of core skills that they need to practise effectively in the classroom and will be able to use various methods and techniques to teach the language skills of listening, speaking, reading and writing in a range of situations.\n\nCertificate in Teaching Chinese as a Foreign Language (TCFL, Level 5)\n\nDuration: 20 weeks (including 2 week term breaks) http://www.nznc.ac.nz/entrtytest.jpg\nThis Chinese teaching certificate course is designed to help teachers in New Zealand schools effectively teach Chinese language and cultural aspects to non-speakers. The course lays a great emphasis on the practical skills required to teach Chinese while taking account of the varied needs of teaching Chinese in primary and secondary schools, and at further adult education institutions as well as in higher education establishments. The course is suitable both as an initial introduction as well as an in service training programme in the teaching of Chinese.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.nznc.ac.nz', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'New Zealand National College (NZNC) is a Private Training Establishment (PTE) that is registered with NZQA and operates under the 1989 Education Amendment Act. The College has a strong commitment to quality in all aspects of its operations and in particular through the provision of quality education programmes and training. Our vision is to be the world-class organisation specialised in second language teaching and learning. Our mission is to provide a high quality language teaching certificate-training programme for second language teaching job seekers throughout the world. The primary focus of the Colleges activities is the achievement of this mission. Accreditation NZNC is accredited by the New Zealand Qualifications Authority (NZQA) as a Private Tertiary Education Provider with accreditation to deliver training courses. NZNC is a signatory to the Code of Practice for the Pastoral Care of International Students published by the Ministry of Education. NZNC is certified by Education o...', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
