 \n\nIndividual highlights of the REF 2014 results include: \n\nSussex History was the highest rated History submission in the UK for the quality of its research outputs \nThe Sussex English submission rose from 31st to 9th across the UK since the last research assessment exercise in 2008\n84 per cent of the University‚Äôs research impact in Psychology was rated as the top possible grade, 4* \nSussex Geography had the most 4* rated research impact of any Geography submission across the UK.\nOverall, the University was placed 36th (of multi-disciplinary institutions) by GPA.', 'Campus life\nSussex has one of the most beautiful campus locations in Britain. Situated in rolling parkland on the edge of Brighton, the campus combines award-winning architecture with green open spaces. The campus is surrounded by the South Downs National Park, but just a few minutes away from the lively city of Brighton & Hove.\n\nDesigned by Sir Basil Spence, the buildings that make up the heart of the campus were given listed building status in 1993. Falmer House is one of only two educational buildings in the UK to be Grade I listed in recognition of its exceptional interest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(237, 'Warnborough College (UK)', 1973, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/warnborough.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/warnborough1.jpg', 'Canterbury , United Kingdom', '18 Lower Bridge St, Canterbury CT1 2LG, United Kingdom', NULL, 'Overall IELTS grade of 6.5 with a minimum of 6.0 in each component, or equivalent.', 'Private', '¬£10,000', 'Business Management\n\nDiploma in Business Management (Level 4)\nHigher Diploma in Business Management (Level 5)\nGraduate Diploma in Business Management (Level 6)\nPostgraduate Diploma in Business Management (Level 7)\nHuman Resource Management\n\nHigher Diploma in Human Resource Management (Level 5)\nGraduate Diploma in Human Resource Management (Level 6)\nMarketing\n\nDiploma in Marketing (Level 4)\nHigher Diploma in Marketing (Level 5)\nGraduate Diploma in Marketing (Level 6)\nTravel, Tourism, Hospitality\n\nDiploma in Travel, Tourism and Hospitality Management (Level 4)\nHigher Diploma in Travel, Tourism and Hospitality Management (Level 5)\nGraduate Diploma in Travel, Tourism and Hospitality Management (Level 6)\nDiploma in Medical Sciences\n\nCreative Workshops\n\nCorporate Training\n\nMini MBA\nVocational and Job Skills', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', '44 1227 762107', 'admission@studymetro.com', '¬£', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://warnborough.ac.uk/', 'https://www.facebook.com/Warnborough-College-UK-1443803552506325/', 'https://twitter.com/warnborough', 'https://plus.google.com/114362408378211660689', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/warnborough-college', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/warnborough-college', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/warnboroughcollege', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Warnborough College (UK)', 'Warnborough College is an accredited British College for Adult Education based in the historic university city of Canterbury. Its roots lie deep in the Oxford tradition of quality academic programmes, personal mentoring, love of learning and intellectual curiosity. Warnborough provides study options leading to British qualifications and career needs: University pathways, English language courses, and corporate and vocational training. Courses are taught in Canterbury, at partner campuses around the world, and through distance learning or blended learning.', 'Thousands of students have gone on to further studies at other educational institutions worldwide, and forged successful careers in all fields. A Warnborough education can be experienced through study here in Canterbury, by distance learning, by blended learning, or through one of our Academic Partners. With our corporate partners, we even take our training into offices and factories.\n\nStudents who study in Canterbury will get the opportunity to experience life in a 2000-year old English city. It is a vibrant and safe university city, close to London, in the beautiful ‚ÄòGarden of England‚Äô. This is a great opportunity to make friends from England and around the world, expand your world view and experience personal growth. As your ‚Äòhome away from home‚Äô, Warnborough College is committed to your success.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(238, 'West London College', 1977, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wlc.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/west-london-college.jpg', ' Manchester St, London, United Kingdom', 'Hannah House 13-, 16 Manchester St, London W1U 4DJ, United Kingdom', NULL, 'Overall IELTS grade of 6.5 with a minimum of 6.0 in each component, or equivalent.', 'Private', '¬£10,000', 'Diploma Courses\nUAL Foundation Diploma in Fashion DesignUAL Foundation Diploma in Fine ArtLevel 4 Diploma in Fashion RetailUAL Foundation Diploma in Interior Design\nSummer Programmes\nSummer Fashion Programmes\nShort Courses\nDevelop a sketchbook inspired by LondonDrawing & painting (20 weeks)Mending \n(4 weeks)Machine embroidery (5 weeks)Hat making \n(5 weeks)Portfolio building through drawing and mixed mediaPattern Cutting\n(2 days)Garment Construction\n(2 days)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', '44 20 7491 1841', 'admission@studymetro.com', '¬£12000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.westlondoncollege.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/westlondoncollege', 'https://twitter.com/WLCnews', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/west-london-college', 'https://www.instagram.com/wlc_foundation_diploma/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/WestLondonCollegeTV', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'West London College', 'West London College is a long-established independent institution with approximately 400 students, mostly aged between 18 and 25, from both the UK and overseas. It is a truly cosmopolitan learning environment.\n\nThe College occupies a superb building in London''s West End, within walking distance of Bond Street, Baker Street and Marble Arch tube stations. Students who are not already London residents are accommodated in student halls of residence, mainly in the Queensway and Bayswater area just a short bus or tube ride away.\n\n', 'All courses are practically-based and taught by experienced industry professionals. Our one year Diploma courses lead to qualifications awarded by the University of the Arts London award body. Each course has been carefully developed or selected for its relevance to the industry and for its international recognition as evidence of professional competence.\n\nTrainers are chosen not just for their technical skills but also for their ability to impart their knowledge to others. They are entertaining and friendly, and always do their best to ensure that the course is as enjoyable as possible.\n\nWorkshops are well-equipped and there is also a quiet library for self-study, as well as a subsidised restaurant, student common rooms and a free 40 station internet cafe. There is, of course, also free wifi throughout the campus.\n\nThe College has regular social events for its student body, such as parties, fashion shows, club nights and boat trips.\n\nAll in all West London College offers excellent programmes in a great learning environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
