(254, 'BERKELEY COLLEGE ', 1931, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/berkeley-college.gif', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/BerkeleyCollegeGrads.jpg', 'New York, NY , United States', ' 3 E 43rd St, New York, NY 10017, United States', NULL, 'Required Documents:\n- Official Transcripts - All Previous Secondary Schools (Minimum 2.75 on a 4.0 scale)\n- TOEFL (61) or IELTS (5.5) or PTE(43) - Official Scores Only\n-  (1) Letter of Recommendation (submitted online) \n- Statement of Purpose (submitted online) \n- Copy of Passport\n- Bank Statement \n- Affidavit of Support\n- Berkeley I-20 Application\n- SAT or ACT- Optional \n- NACES Evaluation NOT Required\n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Bachelor''s Degrees\nLarry L. Luing School of Business¬Æ\nAccounting\nFashion Merchandising and Management\nFinancial Services\nGeneral Business\nHealth Services Management\nInformation Technology Management\nInternational Business\nManagement\nMarketing Communications\nSchool of Health Studies\nNursing\nSchool of Professional Studies\nDesign Management\nGraphic Design\nInterior Design\nJustice Studies - Criminal Justice\nLegal Studies\nNational Security\nAssociate''s Degrees\nLarry L. Luing School of Business¬Æ\nAccounting\nFashion Merchandising and Management\nFinancial Services\nHealth Services Administration\nInformation Technology Management\nInternational Business\nManagement\nMarketing Communications\nSchool of Health Studies\nHealth Sciences\nMedical Assistant\nMedical Insurance, Billing, and Coding\nSurgical Technology            M.B.A., Management  \nM.B.A. Program Statistics      Certificate Programs\nMedical Assistant\nMedical Insurance, Billing, and Coding\nPatient Care Technician\nPractical Nurse\nSurgical Processing Technician', 'Mr. Michael J. Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 212-986-4343', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://berkeleycollege.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/BerkeleyCollegePage', 'https://twitter.com/berkeleycollege', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school?id=20394&trk=edu-cp-title', 'https://www.instagram.com/berkeleycollege/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/berkeleycollege', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/berkeleycollege', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'BERKELEY COLLEGE (2)', 'Since 1931, Berkeley College has specialized in preparing students for professional and personal success. Proven, career-focused Bachelor''s and Associate''s degrees are offered in a diverse range of areas, and the college is widely recognized for providing students with the competitive edge and skills sought by employers. This innovative combination of benefits is known as The Berkeley Advantage¬Æ.\n\nCombining intense classroom instruction with practical hands-on learning, degree programs are carefully developed and regularly updated to ensure marketplace relevancy. Instructors are chosen for their excellent academic credentials, professional experience, and a dedication to delivering close, personal attention to students.\n', 'All degree programs require faculty-monitored internships or job-related assignments as part of the curriculum. This allows students to apply what they''ve learned in real-world situations and give them valuable experience for beginning their career. Programs and courses are divided into three main areas:\n\n1) The Larry L. Luing School of Business accounts for the majority of the programs of study. Rigorous academic programs; a well-qualified, supportive faculty; and a wealth of student services and resources work together to help graduates meet the challenges they will face in today''s rapidly changing global business environment.\n\n2) The School of Professional Studies prepares students for success in careers requiring specialized training. Courses give students the in-depth knowledge and latest skills required to excel as professionals in criminal justice, interior design, legal studies, graphic design, and health services careers.\n\n3) The School of Liberal Arts helps expand students'' knowledge and broaden their awareness of the world around them. Courses in humanities, mathematics/science, social sciences, English, and foreign languages add value to the specialized, career-focused training.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
