(258, 'BROOKLYN COLLEGE - CUNY (NEW YORK)', 1930, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Brooklyn_College_Logo.svg_.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Brooklyn_College.jpg', ' Brooklyn, NY, United States', '2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210, United States', NULL, 'Official Transcripts- All Bachelors Transcripts (Minimum 3.0 on a 4.0 scale)\n     - TOEFL (61) or IELTS (6.0) \n     - GMAT required for Accounting \n     - GRE required for MPH\n     - Statement of Purpose\n     - Resume\n     - (2) Letters of Recommendation\n     - Copy of Passport\n     - NACES Evaluation required\n     - Bank Statement\n     - Affidavit of Support\n     - Brooklyn College I-20 application\n', 'Public', '$10,000', 'Programs\n\nGraduate Programs:\nAutism Spectrum Disorders, Advanced Certificate\nBilingual Education, Advanced Certificate\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Bilingual Education, M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Liberal Arts (Option A), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Liberal Arts (Option B), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Liberal Arts (Option C), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Mathematics (Option B), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Mathematics (Option C), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Mathematics (Option A), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Science and Environmental Education (Option A), M.S. in Ed.\nChildhood Education Teacher (1-6) - Science and Environmental Education (Option C), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of Students with Disabilities Generalist (7-12), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in childhood education (grades 1-6) (Option A), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in childhood education (grades 1-6) (Option B), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in childhood education (grades 1-6) (Option C), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in early childhood education (birth to grade 2) (Option A), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in early childhood education (birth to grade 2) (Option B), M.S. in Ed.\nSpecial Education - Teacher of students with disabilities in early childhood education (birth to grade 2) (Option C), M.S. in Ed.doctoral programs:\n\nBiochemistry\nBiology\nChemistry\nComputer and Information Science (CIS)\nEarth and Environmental Science \nPhysics  ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 718-951-5000', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/brooklyncollege/', 'https://twitter.com/bklyncollege411', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/brooklyn-college?trk=company_logo', 'https://www.instagram.com/bklyncollege411/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/BrooklynCollegeCUNY', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/BrooklynCollegeCUNY', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'BROOKLYN COLLEGE - CUNY (NEW YORK)', '\nBrooklyn College is one of the great New York City area universities and is part of the very popular City of New York (CUNY) institutions. The university is an integral part of the civic, urban and artistic energy of New York and uses the entire city as a living classroom that broadens our students'' understanding of the world around them. \n\nBrooklyn College has a student enrollment of approximately 16,500 students - 13,100 undergraduates and 3,400 graduates who come from 150 counties and speak 105 languages.\n\nThe college offers 120 study abroad, undergraduate and Graduate degree programs in: business, creative arts; humanities; social, behavioral and natural sciences; mathematics and education. Admissions criteria have become increasingly selective over the last decade, with a mean SAT score of 1134 for 2011. More than 4,000 students graduate and receive bachelor''s and master''s degrees each year, as well as advanced certificates, at our last Commencement Exercises.\n', 'Student Life\nStudent life at Brooklyn College is active, diverse and multifaceted. Our students are engaged in more than 100 student clubs and organizations spanning a broad range of cultural, ethnic, community, media, artistic, social action, religious and other special interests. More than one dozen fraternities and sororities bring Greek life to campus. Intramural sports are popular, and the college''s award-winning basketball, cross country, soccer, softball, tennis and volleyball teams compete at the Division III level of the National Collegiate Athletic Association. \n\nBuilding for the Future\nThis spring, the Brooklyn College broke ground for a new center for the performing arts, which will provide a fitting home for its award-winning performance programs. The college is also deep into the planning stages for a new state-of-the-art science complex. \n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
