s Studies\nFoods and Nutrition\nFoods, Nutrition & Community Education\nForensic Science\nFrench\nGlobal Studies\nGraphic Design\nHistory\nLeadership\nLiterary Studies\nMathematics\nMedical Nutrition Therapy for Health Professionals\nMusic\nNutritional Science\nPersonal Fitness Training\nPhilosophy\nPolitical Science\nPsychology\nReligious Studies\nSecondary Education\nSociology\nSpanish\nStudio Art\nVictim Services\nWomen''s Studies\nWriting Studies\nCombined Degree Programs\nB.A. Criminal Justice/M.A. Justice Administration and Public Service\nB.A. Elementary Education/M.A. Education\nB.S. Foods and Nutrition/M.S. Nutrition\nB.S. or B.A./M.S. Management\nB.A. Psychology/M.A. Counseling Psychology (30-credit specialization only)\nB.A. Religious Studies/M.A. Theology\nDual Degree Programs\nB.S. Biology/M.S. Physician Assistant (Le Moyne College)\nB.S. Biology/Doctor of Medicine (AUA College of Medicine)\nB.S. Biology/Doctor of Pharmacy (Pharm.D.) (Saint Joseph College)\nB.S. Biology/Doctor of Physical Therapy (Methodist University)\nB.S. Biology/Doctor of Podiatric Medicine (NY College of Podiatric Medicine)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 973-290-4000', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$30,026', '$35', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.cse.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/CollegeOfSaintElizabeth', 'https://twitter.com/CollegeOfSaintE', 'https://plus.google.com/+collegeofsaintelizabeth', 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school?id=18855', 'https://www.instagram.com/CollegeofSaintE/', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyGYtwhLFiPHtNKhLxfxIEA', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyGYtwhLFiPHtNKhLxfxIEA', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'COLLEGE OF SAINT ELIZABETH', 'The College of Saint Elizabeth, established in 1899, is located in New Jesey''s about 1 hour from New York City. The college is located on a beautiful 200-acre campus and is a leader in the education of working adults, both women and men. The undergraduate programs are exclusively for women. Men are enrolled in Graduate and certificate programs.\n\nThe College offers Baccalaureate degrees and a limited number of Graduate degree and Ph.D programs. Popular undergraduate programs include those in business, chemistry, food & nutrition, health studies, public service, world cultures, justice administration and more. Preparation for ministry is offered through the Center for Ministry and Spirituality.\n\nStudents should have at least a 2.5 GPA (on a 4.00 scale) and have IELTS of 6.0 or TOEFL of 79+. Only hard copy applications are accepted. Interested students can enroll for either the fall (September) or Spring (January) semesters. \n', 'The College''s arts and education building, houses the Therese A. Maloney Art Gallery, the 560-seat Dolan Performance Center, the Holocaust Education Resource Center, as well as the departments of art, music, and theology.\n\nActivities on campus include many student-run organizations and a wide variety of social, cultural, service, and athletic events. Student life at CSE is rich with facilities, services, and resources including: Student Center with renovated dining hall and bookstore, student lounges, Olympic-size pool, gym, fitness center and drama studio\n\nTwo residence halls with study areas, kitchenettes, lounges, convenient parking, and internet and email access from every room are available to all students.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
