ing. Furthermore, its national and international profile continues to grow, and currently students from 37 US states and 25 countries study the academic programs.\n \nStudents can get admission without IELTS/TOEFL and get I20 in 10-14 business working days.  MBA Program is available for 1 and 2 years. \n \nCUC is closely affiliated with Global university Systems (GUS).\n \n \nWhy Choose Concordia University Chicago?\n \n‚Ä¢ Founded in 1864, Concordia-Chicago has a 150-year history of bringing higher education to the world.\n‚Ä¢ More than 4,000 students are enrolled in CUC master‚Äôs and doctoral programs.\n‚Ä¢ Concordia-Chicago ranks 22 out of 7,400 U.S. colleges and universities for high-quality education master‚Äôs and bachelor‚Äôs programs by College Online Database www.onlinecollegesdatabase.org/top-colleges-and-universities-for-teaching \n‚Ä¢ Washington Monthly ranked CUC 96 out of 684 for masters universities in 2013 www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2013/09/09/how-us-news-calculated-the-2014-best-colleges-rankings \n‚Ä¢ US News ranked CUC 83 out of over 156 Midwest universities for 2014 www.colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges/rankings/regional-universities?int=9a3408 \n‚Ä¢ Well located for downtown Chicago\n‚Ä¢ In 2013 CUC had the highest amount of graduates in Illinois.\n‚Ä¢ Fantastic facilities including, athletics, running track, tennis courts fitness center, computer labs, library, beautiful grounds and much more all located on a safe campus.\n‚Ä¢ The opportunity to work ‚Äì International Students are entitled to work 20 hours a week www.uscis.gov/working-united-states/students-and-exchange-visitors/students-and-employment \n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
