(335, 'LASELL COLLEGE', 1851, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Lasell_College.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Lasell.jpg', ' MA  United States', '1844 Commonwealth Avenue, Auburndale, MA 02466, United States', NULL, 'IELTS 6/TOFEL 80', 'Private', '$10,000', NULL, 'Michael B. Alexander', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 617-243-2000', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$30', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.lasell.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/LasellCollege/', 'https://twitter.com/lasellcollege', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/lasellcollege/', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/lasellcollege', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/lasellcollege', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'LASELL COLLEGE', 'An innovator in education for over 150 years, Lasell College today is a comprehensive coeducational college offering professionally oriented bachelor''s and master''s degree programs. Our 50-acre campus is located in suburban Newton, Massachusetts-within eight miles of downtown Boston at the heart of the Route 128 high-tech corridor.\n\nWe are known for helping students make the connection between classroom lessons and real life through hands-on activities such as internships, practicum, service learning, and meaningful projects\nStudent/Faculty Ratio & Class Size\nLasell College faculty are committed to creatively integrating challenging coursework with practical experience in an environment that fosters lifelong intellectual exploration, active citizenship and social responsibility.\n\nClass SizeUndergraduate Student/Faculty ratio: 14:1 \n95% of undergraduate classes have fewer than 25 students \n100% of students undertake an internship in their field of study \n59% of undergraduates participated in Service Learning in 2011-2012 \n78 full-time faculty; 18% minority \n', 'Technology\nOur approach to technology is based on the College''s philosophy of connected learning, infusing the physical and online classroom environment with the most current systems, web sites, and social media.\n\nTechnology Enhanced Classrooms: 98% \nResident Halls equipped with WiFi: 100% \nComputer Labs: 8 \nComputers Available to Students: 150 \nWireless Printing from Personal Laptops: Yes \nPersonal Storage in the Cloud: 25GB \nRegister & View Grades Online: Yes \nSubmit Assignments Online: Yes \nOnline Learning Management System: Moodle \n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(336, 'LEHMAN COLLEGE (CUNY)', 1967, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/cuny-lehman-college_416x416.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/cuny-lehman-college.jpg', ' NY 10468, United States', '250 Bedford Park Blvd W, Bronx, NY 10468, United States', NULL, 'Entrance Requirements- Graduates\n- Application For Admission: Complete online \n- Application Fee - Pay $125 online\n- Official Transcripts- - All previous universities (have attained a minimum undergraduate grade point average of (3.0) in the field selected for the graduate program and a minimum overall grade point average of (2.7) in the undergraduate record.\n- TOEFL (61) IELTS 6.0\n- GRE required for some programs\n- Statement of Purpose\n- Resume\n- (2-3) Letters of Recommendation\n- Copy of Passport\n- NACES Evaluation required\n', 'Public', '$10,000', 'Accounting  ‚Ä¢  \nAdvertising, Creative  ‚Ä¢  \nArts Management  ‚Ä¢  \nAthletic Training  ‚Ä¢  \nCommunication  ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ \nCriminal Justice  ‚Ä¢  \nEducation, General  ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ \nEnglish  ‚Ä¢  \nEntrepreneurship  ‚Ä¢  \nEnvironmental Science/Studies  ‚Ä¢  \nExercise Science  ‚Ä¢  \nFashion Design  ‚Ä¢  \nFinance  ‚Ä¢  \nGraphic Design  ‚Ä¢  \nHistory  ‚Ä¢  \nHospitality Management  ‚Ä¢  \nHuman Services  ‚Ä¢  \nHumanities  ‚Ä¢  \nInternational Business  ‚Ä¢  \nJournalism  ‚Ä¢  \nLegal Studies  ‚Ä¢  \nManagement  ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ \nMarketing  ‚Ä¢  \nMathematics  ‚Ä¢  \nMultimedia  ‚Ä¢  \nPre-Law  ‚Ä¢  \nPsychology  ‚Ä¢  \nPublic Relations and Corporate Comm.  ‚Ä¢  \nRadio  ‚Ä¢  \nSociology  ‚Ä¢  \nSports Communication  ‚Ä¢  \nSports Management  ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ \nUndecidedUndecided, Education, General . Managemen', 'Jos√© Luis Cruz', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 718-960-8000', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$14,000', '$65', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.lehman.cuny.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/LehmanCUNY/', 'https://twitter.com/@LehmanCollege', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lehman-college', 'https://www.instagram.com/lehmancuny/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LehmanCollege', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LehmanCollege', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'LEHMAN COLLEGE (CUNY)', 'With more than 60,000 alumni and 12,000 students, Lehman College serves the Bronx and our surrounding region as an intellectual, economic, and cultural center. The College is named after Herbert H. Lehman, who was governor of New York State, a U.S. Senator, and an internationalist. His values of dedicated public service continue to guide the College today.', 'Since it was first constructed in 1931, this campus has been a destination for those seeking knowledge; first as a home for the uptown branch of Hunter College, and for the last forty-three years, home to Herbert H. Lehman College, where we have built upon the traditions of the campus and further expanded the City University of New York‚Äôs mission in the Bronx.\nSince 1968, Lehman has provided the gateway to a better life for more than 62,000 alumni. Old and young, American-born and immigrants, and members of every race and religion have walked through our doors, strolled our tranquil green walkways, and studied within both the buildings we inherited and the new ones we have added ‚Äî and are still adding ‚Äî to this historic campus.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
