(338, 'LIM College', 1939, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LIM_Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LIM-.jpg', 'NY , United States', '12 E 53rd St, New York, NY 10022, United States', NULL, 'IELTS 6/TOFEL 80', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Business Administration   ‚Ä¢ \nFashion Merchandising  ‚Ä¢  \nInternational Business  ‚Ä¢  \nManagement  ‚Ä¢  \nProfessional Studies   ‚Ä¢ \nVisual MerchandisingProfessional Studies , Business Adminstratiin ', 'Elizabeth S. Marcuse', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 212-752-1530', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$24,225', '$40', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'https://www.limcollege.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/LIMCollege', 'https://twitter.com/LIMCollege', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/lim-college-32891', 'https://www.instagram.com/limcollege/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LIM1939', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LIM1939', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'LIM College', 'The college was founded in 1939 by Maxwell F. Marcuse as the Laboratory Institute of Merchandising, at the request of retailers who wanted a school that would teach students about the fashion business and merchandising. Maxwell Marcuse''s son, Adrian G. Marcuse, was president from 1972 to 2002, succeeded by Elizabeth S. Marcuse.[2][3] In 2009, the school changed its name to LIM College.[2][4]', 'LIM College educates students for success in the global business of fashion and its many related industries. As a pioneer in experiential education, LIM College fosters a unique connection between real-world experience and academic study in business principles. Developing students‚Äô creative and critical thinking, as well as leadership skills, an LIM College education empowers students to become accomplished professionals in a highly competitive, dynamic business environment as well as responsible citizens of a global society.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
