 of the Louisiana State University System, and the largest institution of higher education in Louisiana in terms of student enrollment. In 2015, the university enrolled over 26,000 undergraduate and over 5,000 graduate students in 14 schools and colleges. Several of LSU''s graduate schools, such as the E.J. Ourso College of Business and the Paul M. Hebert Law Center, have received national recognition in their respective fields of study.[8] Designated as a land-grant, sea-grant and space-grant institution, LSU is also noted for its extensive research facilities, operating some 800 sponsored research projects funded by agencies such as the National Institutes of Health, the National Science Foundation, the National Endowment for the Humanities, and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration.[9][10]\nLSU''s athletics department fields teams in 21 varsity sports (9 men''s, 12 women''s), and is a member of the NCAA (National Collegiate Athletic Association) and the SEC (Southeastern Conference). The university is represented by its mascot, Mike the Tiger.', 'The Louisiana State University (officially Louisiana State University and Agricultural and Mechanical College, often referred to as LSU) is a public coeducational university located in Baton Rouge, Louisiana.[7] The university was founded in 1853 in what is now known as Pineville, Louisiana, under the name Louisiana State Seminary of Learning & Military Academy. The current LSU main campus was dedicated in 1926, consists of more than 250 buildings constructed in the style of Italian Renaissance architect Andrea Palladio, and occupies a 650-acre (2.6 km¬≤) plateau on the banks of the Mississippi River.\nLSU is the flagship institution of the Louisiana State University System, and the largest institution of higher education in Louisiana in terms of student enrollment. In 2015, the university enrolled over 26,000 undergraduate and over 5,000 graduate students in 14 schools and colleges. Several of LSU''s graduate schools, such as the E.J. Ourso College of Business and the Paul M. Hebert Law Center, have received national recognition in their respective fields of study.[8] Designated as a land-grant, sea-grant and space-grant institution, LSU is also noted for its extensive research facilities, operating some 800 sponsored research projects funded by agencies such as the National Institutes of Health, the National Science Foundation, the National Endowment for the Humanities, and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration.[9][10]\nLSU''s athletics department fields teams in 21 varsity sports (9 men''s, 12 women''s), and is a member of the NCAA (National Collegiate Athletic Association) and the SEC (Southeastern Conference). The university is represented by its mascot, Mike the Tiger.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(344, 'MANHATTAN INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT', NULL, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/manhattan-institute-of-management.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/manhattan-institute-of-management-8.jpg', 'NY , United States', '110 William St, New York, NY 10038, United States', NULL, 'Entrance Requirements- Graduates (MBA Program)\n- Application For Admission: Complete online \n- Application Fee - Pay $ 100 online\n- Official Transcripts- All previous Secondary Schools (Minimum 2.75 on a 4.0 scale)\n- TOEFL (79) or IELTS (6.5) \n- GMAT required for the MBA\n- GRE required for some programs\n- Statement of Purpose\n- Resume\n- (3) Letters of Recommendation\n- Copy of Passport\n- NACES Evaluation required\n', 'Private', '$10,000', '\nMAJOR ASSOCIATE BACHELORS MASTERS DOCTORAL\nBusiness Administration/Management   ‚Ä¢ \nConditional Admission  ‚Ä¢  \nMBA', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 212-796-6115', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$30', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.mimusa.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/mimusa.ny/', 'https://twitter.com/mim_usa', 'https://plus.google.com/+MimusaEdu', 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/manhattan-institute-of-management-162149', 'https://www.instagram.com/manhattaninstituteofmanagement/', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCIxmAONJI5c9zNjjYx1LKcA', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCIxmAONJI5c9zNjjYx1LKcA', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'MANHATTAN INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT', 'Manhattan Institute of Management (MIM) is located right in heart of downtown New York City, the financial capital of the world.\n\nMIM has two great, one year (12 month) MBA programs. These are located in NYC and Spain.\n\n- New York City- All MBA courses taken right in New York City by Wall Street.\nor,...\n- Spain- An integrated program where course are taken both in NYC and in Spain.O\n\nIf you have seen pictures of the New York Stock Exchange and the famous statue of the big Bull outside the exchange,.. then you will know MIM is located right there. MIM is in a very exciting, historical location in NYC and offers students many option for studying, traveling and finding work positions. The MBA program is fully accredited by the New York State Department of Education and attracts international students from all part of the world. \n\nMIM offers a very strong MBA program in NYC and classes are held in a major building. Students find places to live in NYC and spend class time in lower Manhattan with great professors and sucessful business people from major NYC companies. \n', 'The Manhattan Institute of Management is a private institution committed to offering students a high quality, global business education. MIM offers students a real opportunity to gain insight into the meaning of business success, in New York and around the world. In the past 26 years, over 5,000 students from almost every country on earth have stepped through the gates of MIM''s downtown Manhattan main campus.\n\nThe advantages of studying at MIM include:\n\nA Global Business Education program International MBA (with partners) \nWall Street Location Intensive Solar Technology Management \nInnovative, Affordable Programs Business Certificate Programs \nBuild Your Future In Company Training Program (ICTP) \n\nThe Manhattan Institute of Management is a non-profit institution that is approved by: VESID, Workforce, and the Trade Act.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(345, 'Manhattanville College', 1841, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Manhattanville_College_1061908.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Manhattanville-College.jpg', 'Purchase, NY , United States', '2900 Purchase St, Purchase, NY 10577, United States', NULL, 'Required Documents:\n     - Official Transcripts- All previous Universities \n     - TOEFL (85) \n     - (3) Letters of Recommendation\n     - Copy of Passport\n     - Bank Statement showing $46,260\n     - Affidavit of Support\n     - WES Evaluation Required \n     - $400 deposit required after admission for I-20 to be issued. \n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'http://www.mville.edu/academics', 'Michael Geisler', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 914-694-2200', 'admission@studymetro.com', 'UG- Per sem-$4,340                                                                Masters: Per credit- $1000', '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.mville.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/Manhattanville', 'https://twitter.com/Mville_College', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/manhattanville_college/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ManhattanvilleVideo', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ManhattanvilleVideo', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Manhattanville College', 'Manhattanville College is a private, coeducational liberal arts college offering undergraduate and graduate degrees, located in Purchase, New York. Founded in 1841 at 412 Houston Street in Manhattan, it was known initially as Manhattanville College of the Sacred Heart. Manhattanville''s mission is to "educate students to become ethically and socially responsible leaders for the global community".[1] The school moved to its current location in Purchase, New York in 1952.\nApproximately 1,700 undergraduate and 1,000 graduate students attend Manhattanville. Manhattanville students come from 76 countries and 48 states.".[2]\n', 'The architectural and administrative centerpiece of the Manhattanville campus, Reid Hall (1864) is named after Whitelaw Reid, owner of the New York Tribune. On either side of Reid Hall stand academic buildings on one side and on the other residence halls around a central quad designed by Frederick Law Olmsted, the designer of Central Park. The Manhattanville community regards the central quad and buildings as representing the academic vision of the college‚Äôs commitment to integrated learning and centered strengths. Other historic buildings include Lady Chapel, the President‚Äôs Cottage known as the Barbara Debs House, the old Stables, and Water Tower.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
