(355, 'Midwestern State University', 1922, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Midwestern-State-University.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Midwestern-State-University-BG-1.jpg', 'Wichita Falls, Texas, U.S.', '3410 Taft Blvd, Wichita Falls, TX 76308, United States', NULL, 'IELTS 6/TOFEL 80', 'Public', '$10,000 USD per year aprox', 'Biology\nMS\nBusiness Administration\nMBA\nClinical Mental Health \n\nMA\nComputer Science\n\nMS\nCriminal Justice\nMACJ\nCurriculum and Instruction\nMED\nEducational Leadership\nMED\nEducational Technology\nMED\nEnglish\nMA\nExercise Physiology\nMSEP\nFamily Nurse Practitioner\nMSN\nFamily Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioner\nMSN\nGeoscience\nMS\nHealth Services Administration\nMHA\nHistory\nMA\nHuman Resources Development\nMA\nNurse Educator\nMSN\nPolitical Science\nMA\nPsychology\nMA\nRadiologic Administration\nMSRS\nRadiologic Education\nMSRS\nRadiologist Assistant\nMSRS\nReading Education\nMED\nSchool Counseling\nMED\nSpecial Education\nMED\nSport Administration\nMED\nTraining and Development\nMA\n', 'Suzanne Shipley', '6043', NULL, NULL, 'Off campus & on campus ', '1 940-397-4000', 'admission@studymetro.com', '$7,753 / sem', '$25', NULL, ' Fall \nSpring \nSummer ', 'https://www.mwsu.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/MidwesternState ', 'https://twitter.com/midwesternstate ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/user/MidwesternState ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/MidwesternState ', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Midwestern State University', 'Midwestern State University is a public liberal arts college in Wichita Falls, Texas and a member of the Council of Public Liberal Arts Colleges. In 2015, it had over 6,000 students. Midwestern is one of four independent public universities in Texas unaffiliated with a state public university system. It is the state''s only public liberal arts college.\nFounded in 1922 as Wichita Falls Junior College, it was renamed Hardin Junior College in 1937 when it moved to its present location off Taft Boulevard. In 1946, a senior division was added and it was renamed Hardin College. In January 1950, the name changed to Midwestern University, the junior college division remaining Hardin Junior College. In these years, wider recognition came to the school. In March 1948, the University became a member of the Association of Colleges and Secondary Schools. In January 1959, the University added a Graduate School which received full approval from the State Board of Education in August of that year.\n', 'Midwestern State University is a public liberal arts college in Wichita Falls, Texas and a member of the Council of Public Liberal Arts Colleges. In 2015, it had over 6,000 students. Midwestern is one of four independent public universities in Texas unaffiliated with a state public university system. It is the state''s only public liberal arts college.\nFounded in 1922 as Wichita Falls Junior College, it was renamed Hardin Junior College in 1937 when it moved to its present location off Taft Boulevard. In 1946, a senior division was added and it was renamed Hardin College. In January 1950, the name changed to Midwestern University, the junior college division remaining Hardin Junior College. In these years, wider recognition came to the school. In March 1948, the University became a member of the Association of Colleges and Secondary Schools. In January 1959, the University added a Graduate School which received full approval from the State Board of Education in August of that year.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
