'https://www.facebook.com/RiderUniversity', 'https://twitter.com/RiderUniversity', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school?id=18870', 'https://www.instagram.com/rider_university/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/RiderUniversityWeb', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/RiderUniversityWeb', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'RIDER UNIVERSITY', 'Rider University is a comprehensive private university of nearly 6,000 students who are interested in undergraduate and Graduate programs in business, education, liberal arts and sciences, music and the fine and performing arts. \n\nRider in located in Lawrenceville, New Jersey and is approximately 1 hour away from New York City. It has a modern campus and everything students need are right on the campus. Campus housing is available for all students.\n\nThe academic experience emphasize connected learning, leadership skills, a global perspective, social responsibility and a student-centered focus in all areas of study.\n\nOriginally founded in 1865 as a business college to prepare professionals for programs in Business Administration; Liberal Arts, Education, and Sciences; College of Continuing Studies; and School of Education. The university offers graduate and undergraduate students alike the rich hands-on experiences they need to prepare for a professional career.\n', '\nRider boasts a student-to-teacher ratio of just 12 to 1, and 96 percent of its faculty members hold the Ph.D. or terminal degree in their field. The University is accredited by the Middle States Commission on Higher Education and holds specialized accreditation with the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB), the National Council for the Accreditation of Teacher Education (NCATE), the National Association of Schools of Music (NASM), the Council for Accreditation of Counseling and Related Education Programs (CACREP), and the National Accreditation of School Psychologists (NASP). Rider is also on the approved list of the American Association of University Women and the American Chemical Society.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
