orts  ', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sam-houston-state-university', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKfJV7HQ7sw23LGbBvTxQJQ ', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKfJV7HQ7sw23LGbBvTxQJQ ', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Sam Houston State University', 'Sam Houston State University (known as SHSU or Sam) was founded in 1879 and is the third oldest public institution of higher learning in the State of Texas. It is located approximately one hour north of downtown Houston in the hills, lakes, and forests region of East Texas in Huntsville. It is one of the oldest purpose-built institutions for the instruction of teachers west of the Mississippi River and the first such institution of its type in Texas. The school is named for Sam Houston, who made his home in the city and is buried there.', 'Sam Houston State University (known as SHSU or Sam) was founded in 1879 and is the third oldest public institution of higher learning in the State of Texas. It is located approximately one hour north of downtown Houston in the hills, lakes, and forests region of East Texas in Huntsville. It is one of the oldest purpose-built institutions for the instruction of teachers west of the Mississippi River and the first such institution of its type in Texas. The school is named for Sam Houston, who made his home in the city and is buried there.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(401, 'SAN DIEGO FLIGHT TRAINING INTERNATIONAL', NULL, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/SAN-DIEGO-FLIGHT-TRAINING-INTERNATIONAL-logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/SAN-DIEGO-FLIGHT-TRAINING-INTERNATIONAL-back-ground.jpg', 'USA ', '8745 Aero Dr #103, San Diego, CA 92123, United States', NULL, '‚Ä¢ English Proficiency\nMinimum of IELTS 5.5 band is required with no band less than 5.0.\n\nStudents can also get admission on the basis of EPC letter.\nFilled application form\n\nEnglish Proficiency proof\n\nCopy of passport\n\nSSC mark-sheet and certificate\n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Commercial Pilot License with Multi Engine Endorsement and Multi Engine Instrument Rating (CPLMEIR) CRICOS CODE: 050124G\nThis is our most popular course and provides you with the minimum qualifications you need to apply to an Airline.\n\nDiploma of Aviation (Flight Operations: AVI50408) including Certificate IV in Aviation (Commercial Pilot)\n\nCRICOS CODE: 077244K (Diploma) & 077243M (Certificate IV)\n\nThe Diploma of Aviation is effectively the same as the Commercial Pilot License with Multi Engine Endorsement and Multi Engine Instrument Rating; however with a little extra administration (which adds to the cost) you can be issued a Diploma. For most of our clients a Diploma is not necessary however there are a few countries and employers that prefer applicants to have a Diploma. If this is the case for you, then the Diploma of Aviation may be the right option.\n\nCommercial Pilot Licence (CPL)\n\nCRICOS CODE: 050123G\nTo fly professionally (i.e to get paid) you must have a CPL. There are a few jobs where a CPL is sufficient however most employers do expect you to have a Multi Engine Endorsement and Instrument Rating as well. Some of our students choose to start with the CPL and decide later on what further training to undertake.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Off Campus & on campus ', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', 'San Diego Flight Training International require an initial US$500 Course deposit \n\nCommercial Pilot License with Instrument Rating = $ 40,590 (Payable', '$60 USD ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'SAN DIEGO FLIGHT TRAINING INTERNATIONAL', 'The core purpose and values of SDFTI have remained unchanged since launching in 1989. These words live in every briefing room, flight deck, instructor and members of the support staff. We are more than a business ... we are part of the history and future of aviation. Producing safe professional pilots is our contribution.  \nSan Diego Flight Training International conducts all flight operations from Montgomery Field (MYF).  The primary offices are located at 8745 Aero Dr. San Diego.\nThis institute has been training pilots in the San Diego area for over 20 years.  The campus is situated directly across Aero Drive from Montgomery Field Municipal Airport in Southern California where our flight line of 17 aircraft and maintenance hangers are located.\nMontgomery Field is a tower-controlled high traffic volume airport central to a very complex airspace that will prepare you for any airports and conditions you will find in your career.\nThe climate, topography and complex airspace create a spectacular training environment; one with an ideal mix of weather for the best experience possible. This allows for much more comfortable training than is available in Arizona and Florida.\nThe campus is centrally located in San Diego in close proximity to reasonably-priced apartments, stores and restaurants\n', 'The core purpose and values of SDFTI have remained unchanged since launching in 1989. These words live in every briefing room, flight deck, instructor and members of the support staff. We are more than a business ... we are part of the history and future of aviation. Producing safe professional pilots is our contribution.  \nSan Diego Flight Training International conducts all flight operations from Montgomery Field (MYF).  The primary offices are located at 8745 Aero Dr. San Diego.\nThis institute has been training pilots in the San Diego area for over 20 years.  The campus is situated directly across Aero Drive from Montgomery Field Municipal Airport in Southern California where our flight line of 17 aircraft and maintenance hangers are located.\nMontgomery Field is a tower-controlled high traffic volume airport central to a very complex airspace that will prepare you for any airports and conditions you will find in your career.\nThe climate, topography and complex airspace create a spectacular training environment; one with an ideal mix of weather for the best experience possible. This allows for much more comfortable training than is available in Arizona and Florida.\nThe campus is centrally located in San Diego in close proximity to reasonably-priced apartments, stores and restaurants\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(402, 'San Ignacio College', NULL, 'USA', ' http://www.htir.co.in/san-ignacio-college-logo/', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/San-Ignacio-College-back-ground.jpg', 'USA ', '3905 NW 107th Ave #301, Doral, FL 33178, United States', 'Licensing Agency\nSan Ignacio College is licensed by the Florida Department of Education‚Äôs Commission for Independent Education. For further information, please go to: www.fldoe.org\n\nAccrediting Agency\nSan Ignacio College is accredited by the Accrediting Council for Independent Colleges and Schools for issuing certificates, diplomas and associate degrees. ACICS is a nationally recognized accrediting agency in the United States. For further information, please go to: www.acics.org\n', 'International Students\n\nLeaving your home, and going to another country can be exciting, but at the same time it can also be challenging. San Ignacio College wants to fully develop you so that you can fulfill your educational and professional goals.\nHow do I apply to San Ignacio College?\nIn order to complete the admissions process, the candidate must meet and submit the following requirements:\nSteps:\nCompleted signed and dated international Admissions Form.\nApplication fee of $150 dollars (non-refundable) made payable to San Ignacio College.\nPayment of the registration fee in the amount of $1,600 for the Culinary Program or $875 for Marketing, International Business, Hospitality Management and Business programs must be paid in full before the I-20 is processed (payment is fully refundable if Visa is denied).\nFinancial statement or certified bank letter in English demonstrating full tuition funds available, along with living expenses capability to cover a minimum of one year (12 months) of tuition and fees, books and supplies, living and any other necessary expenses during your studies. (Amounts must be in or converted to USD currency).\nAffidavit of support form in case of sponsor.\nHigh School diploma translated into English. For undergraduate transfer students, transcripts and educational credentials if they are not in English must be translated.\nIf a student‚Äôs native language is not English, proficiency in English must be established by one of the following options:\n‚ÄîSatisfactory Standardized Test Score as PTE (54), TOEFL (70 - IBT) or IELTS (6.0).\n‚ÄîSan Ignacio College English Test.\n‚ÄîProof of graduating from a college or high school where English is the primary mode of instruction.\n‚ÄîCompleting an ESL program at an institution that is recognized by the U.S. Department of Education.\n‚ÄîCompleting an ESL program at San Ignacio College.\nCopy of a valid passport (upon admissions).\nCopy of SEVIS / I-901 Receipt www.fmjfee.com.\n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'MBA - Master in Business Administration\n \nProgram Objectives:\nUpon completion of the Master in Business Administration and selection of one specialization, students will have the capacity to:\nRead more\nMaster of Arts in Education\nThe Master‚Äôs in Education program offers study of development, intervention, learning and teaching processes in preschool, kindergarten, primary grade levels and educational leadership.\nRead more\nMaster of Arts in Hospitality Management\nStudents will be able to learn the skills that join food and commerce. The program develops the managerial, financial, marketing and gastronomic skills needed for a successful career. \nRead more\nBS in Culinary Arts\n \nProgram Description\nRead more\nBA in Hospitality Management\nThe BA in Hospitality Management is ideal for service-oriented individuals with an entrepreneurial spirit and good commercial instincts.\nRead more\nBA in Marketing\nIn the current competitive environment, marketing is a crucial component of organizations throughout the world. \nRead more\nBA in International Business\nIt is difficult to think of an organization that is not directly or indirectly involved in business or international trade. \nRead more\nBA in Business Administration\nCurrently, organizations seek professionals who are able to identify opportunities to grow their business and who are bold enough to propose and execute ideas.\nRead more\nAA In Early Childhood Education\nThis program adds depth in philosophy, theory, and practice of classroom teaching in general education and special education.\nRead more\nAA in International Business\nThis program allows the students to develop insights into the international business field, while learning about the concepts of commercial transactions between two or more countries and understanding the difference between a local and an international operation.\nRead more\nAA in Hospitality Management\nThe AA in Hospitality Management is ideal for service-oriented individuals with an entrepreneurial spirit and good commercial instincts.\nRead more\nAA in Marketing\nIn the current competitive environment, marketing is a crucial component of organizations throughout the world. \nRead more\nAS in Culinary Arts\nDuration of Program: 64 weeks /16 Months / 4 Semesters.\nRead more\nAA in Business Administration\nCurrently, organizations seek professionals who are able to identify opportunities to grow their business and who are bold enough to propose and execute ideas.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Off Campus & on campus ', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', 'US$ 41,100.00', '$60 USD ', NULL, 'January - May - September', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H-HNqv6ph-Y\n', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H-HNqv6ph-Y\n', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'San Ignacio College', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
