portunities for students to live, travel and work on and near the campus. \n\n', 'St. John''s is popular because of its New York location (15 minutes to NYC), large campus, very strong academic programs and international reputation for producing successful students. The 100-acre Queens campus has broad lawns, tree-lined paths, stone buildings, and magnificent new student residence halls.\n\nThe Staten Island campus occupies a 19th-century estate on a bluff overlooking the New York City harbor. The 18.5-acre campus has neo-Georgian buildings and modern facilities, including the new Kelleher Center. Apartment-style student residences are adjacent to campus.\n\nThe Manhattan campus occupies an award-winning, 10-story building in the city''s bustling Financial Center. Wall Street, Battery Park City, and the Stock Exchange are within walking distance. A limited number of student residences are available here.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
