nging two styles of education-traditional liberal arts and sciences programs and conservatory-based arts programs-into close contact on one campus, the founders of Purchase College hoped to inspire an appreciation for both intellectual and artistic talents in all students. \n\n', 'Purchase College today enjoys a world-class reputation for its arts programs and high rankings for its liberal arts and sciences programs. The college attracts students and faculty from around the world seeking a place where they can develop their talents, expand their minds, and prepare for a life of creative independence.\n\nWith students from 35 different countries, and 65% of the student body living on campus, SUNY Purchase inspires learning in a diverse and intellectual environment.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(437, 'SUNY -NASSAU COMMUNITY COLLEGE', NULL, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nassau-Community-College-logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nassau-Community-College.jpg', ' GARDEN CITY, NEW YORK ', 'ONE EDUCATION DRIVE, GARDEN CITY, NEW YORK 11530-6793', NULL, 'Entrance Requirements- Undergraduates\n- Application For Admission: Complete Hard copy\n- Application Fee - Pay $50 \n- Official Transcripts- All previous Secondary Schools (Minimum 2.0 on a 4.0 scale)\n- TOEFL (Not Required) or IELTS (Not Required) - Placement Tests Only\n- Personal Statement\n- SAT or ACT scores- Optional\n- Copy of Passport\n- Bank Statement \n- Affidavit of Support\n- WES Evaluation Required for all Indian applicants\n', 'Public', '$10,000', 'Accounting ‚Ä¢   \nActing ‚Ä¢   \nAdolescence Education ‚Ä¢   \nAfricana Studies ‚Ä¢   \nArt ‚Ä¢   \nBiology ‚Ä¢   \nBusiness Administration ‚Ä¢   \nChemistry ‚Ä¢   \nCommunication ‚Ä¢   \nComputer Science ‚Ä¢   \nCriminal Justice ‚Ä¢   \nDance ‚Ä¢   \nEarly Childhood Ed and Teaching ‚Ä¢   \nEnglish ‚Ä¢   \nFashion Buying and Merchandising ‚Ä¢   \nFashion Design ‚Ä¢   \nFire Science ‚Ä¢   \nForeign Language ‚Ä¢   \nHealth Sciences ‚Ä¢   \nHuman Services ‚Ä¢   \nInterdisciplinary Studies ‚Ä¢   \nInterior Design ‚Ä¢   \nLegal Studies ‚Ä¢   \nLiberal Arts and Sciences/Liberal Studies ‚Ä¢   \nMarketing ‚Ä¢   \nMathematics ‚Ä¢   \nMedia Studies ‚Ä¢   \nMusic ‚Ä¢   \nNursing ‚Ä¢   \nParalegal Studies ‚Ä¢   \nPhilosophy ‚Ä¢   \nPhotography ‚Ä¢   \nPhysical Education ‚Ä¢   \nPsychology ‚Ä¢   \nRadiation Therapy ‚Ä¢   \nReading Teacher ‚Ä¢   \nRespitory Care ‚Ä¢   \nRetail Merchandising ‚Ä¢   \nTheatre ‚Ä¢', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '516.572.7501', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.ncc.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/nassaucommunitycollege', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/nassaucommunitycollege/', NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'SUNY -NASSAU COMMUNITY COLLEGE', 'Nassau Community College (NCC) is a very popular, 2-year community college and is part of the recognized New York State University (SUNY) system. NCC serves some 20,000 students of all ages and backgrounds and offers day, evening, weekend, continuing and professional programs from its 225-acre campus on Long Island. NCC is located on Long Island just 40 minutes by train from New York City.\n\nAll applicants applying to NCC are accepted with or without a TOEFL or IELLTS. At NCC students find some of the best faculty available and the latest technology in teaching. Many international students start at NCC because of its good reputation, ease to gain admission, lower cost and ability to transfer to a 4-year university to secure a Bachelors degree. Here, students complete their Associate degree and then transfer after two years to a 4 year university to secure their Bachelor degree. Many 4 year universities are impressed with NCC graduates and their acceptance rate is very high.\n', 'Nassau Community College has everything needed for an education that students are looking for. At NCC, students find themselves surrounded by 225 acres that feel more like a four-year college campus than a community college. NCC is the largest single-campus community college in New York state and has a strong mix of quality academics, activities, athletics, arts, and much more. Students come from nearly 60 different countries and speak 35 languages. Although its campus atmosphere is global, NCC keeps its class sizes small. Students get the attention that feels just right, from faculty who are as accomplished in their fields as they are dedicated to students success.\n\nThere are no on campus residence halls at NCC and so all students look to find a place to live off campus.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(438, 'SUNY Polytechnic Institute', 1966, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Sunypolyseal.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Sunypoly.jpg', ' Utica, NY , United States', '100 Seymour Ave, Utica, NY 13502, United States', NULL, 'Required Documents:\n     - Official Transcripts- All previous Universities (Minimum 3.0 on 4.0 scale) \n     - TOEFL (79), IELTS (6.5) or PTE (53) \n     - (1) Letters of Recommendation\n     - Resume\n     - Statement of Purpose \n     - GRE required for all Computer Science and Engineering applicants\n     - Copy of Passport\n     - Bank Statement\n     - No More than 7 backlogs accepted \n     - NACES Evaluation (course-by-course with GPA) required\n', 'Public', '$10,000', 'Accounting\nArt\nArt Teacher Education\nBusiness Administration\nChemical Engineering 3 + 2\nChemistry\nChemistry Teacher\nCounseling\nEnglish\nGraphic Design\nHistory\nHuman Computer Interaction\nMath Education\nMedia Studies\nMental Health Clinician\nPhyiscs Engineering 3+2\nPhysical Therapy 3 +3\nPre-Optometry\nSchool Psychology\nSpecial Education\nTeacher Education-Vocational, Industrial, Technical\n', 'Alain E. Kaloyeros', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 315-792-7100', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'https://www.sunypoly.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/sunypolytechnic', 'https://twitter.com/SUNYPolyInst', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/c/sunyit', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/sunyit', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'SUNY Polytechnic Institute', 'The State University of New York Polytechnic Institute, commonly referred to as SUNY Polytechnic Institute or SUNY Poly,[5] is a public research university with campuses in the town of Marcy in the Utica-Rome metropolitan area and Albany, New York. Founded in 1966 using classrooms at a primary school,[6] SUNY Poly is New York''s public polytechnic college.[7] The Marcy campus, formerly the SUNY Institute of Technology, has a Utica, New York mailing address and was established in 1987. The Albany campus was formerly a component of the University at Albany, established in January 2003.', 'SUNY Poly is accredited by the Middle States Association of Colleges and Schools.[8] The university offers over 30 bachelor''s degrees, 15 master''s degrees, and three doctoral degrees within five different colleges. SUNY Poly students come from across the state of New York, throughout the United States, and more than twenty other nations. More than 25,000 alumni enjoy successful careers in a wide range of fields.[9]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
