(440, 'TENNESSEE TECH UNIVERSITY', 1915, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/ttu_logo_2.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/TennesseeTechUniversity.jpg', 'Cookeville, TN , United States', '1 William L Jones Dr, Cookeville, TN 38505, United States', NULL, 'Required Documents\n     - Official Transcripts- All Bachelors Transcripts (Minimum 2.75 on a 4.0 scale)\n     - TOEFL (79 ), IELTS (6.0), PTE (53) \n     - GRE required for all masters programs \n     - Statement of Purpose\n     - Resume\n     - (3) Letters of Recommendation\n     - Copy of Passport\n     - Bank Statement\n     - Affidavit of Support\n     - NACES Evaluation required for all MBA applicants \n', 'Public', '$10,000', 'Accounting\nAgriculture\nBiology\nBiology/Biomedical Science\nBusiness Administration/Management\nCellular and Molecular Biology\nChemical Engineering\nChemistry\nCivil Engineering\nCommunication\nComputer Science\nComputer Science Engineering\nConditional Admission\nEarth Science\nEcology\nEconomics\nEducation-Health and PE\nElectrical Engineering\nElectrical Engineering (computer option)\nElectrical/Electronic Engineering\nEngineering Technology\nEngineering, General\nEnglish\nEnvironmental Biology\nEnvironmental Engineering\nEnvironmental Science/Studies\nExercise & Sports Science\nFinance\nFrench\nGeosciences\nGerman\nHistory\nIndustrial Engineering\nInformation Assurance and Cybersecurity\nInterdisciplinary Studies\nInternational Business\nManagement\nManufacturing Engineering\nMarketing\nMathematics\nMBA\nMechanical Engineering\nMusic\nMusic Education\nNursing\nPhysics\nPolitical Science\nPre-Dental\nPre-Law\nPre-Medicine\nPre-Occupational Therapy\nPre-Optometry\nPre-Pharmacy\nPre-Physical Therapy\nProfessional Studies\nPsychology\nSecondary Education\nSociology\nSoftware Development/Web Development\nSpanish\nSpecial Education\nTeacher Education-Art\nUndecided (academic exploration program)\nWeb Design\nWildlife Science\n', ' Philip B. Oldham', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 931-372-3101', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'https://www.tntech.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/tennesseetech', 'https://twitter.com/tennesseetech', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/tntechuniversity/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ttunews', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ttunews', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'TENNESSEE TECH UNIVERSITY', 'Tennessee Tech University is a Public university offering many Bachelor and Masters degree programs (and several Ph.D programs) for almost 11,000 students. International students enroll from over 60 countries. The university offers 44 bachelor''s and 20 graduate degree programs in areas like: Business, Engineering, Agricultural and Human Sciences, Arts and Sciences and Education. \n\nThe Princeton Review rates TTU one of the best universities in the Southeast of the US and offers students a great college experience. Students have many options including Division I athletics, Student government, a new fitness center, and over 200 clubs and organizations. There are 15 residence halls and over 300 apartments on campus for students to live.\n\n', 'Small Classes, Great Teachers!\nMore than half of all classes have fewer than 25 students. That means students are more than just a number here and that strong faculty/staff relationships are typical of an education at TTU. Students are immersed in experiential learning. They learn to write and direct plays, build robots, help cardiac patients with nutrition, improve nanotechnology, and more. Students have the opportunity to join a Learning Village that will offer smaller, caring groups led by faculty within the larger community. TTU is the first public university in the state to offer these communities in which a student can become a lifetime member.\n\nA Beautiful Place to Call Home\nLocated in Cookeville, Tennessee, a town of about 25,000 residents, TTU offers the best of both rural and urban living. Situated near scenic state parks like Burgess Falls and Fall Creek Falls the campus is just an hour from three large cities:- Nashville, Knoxville, and Chattanooga.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
