(449, 'Tribeca Flashpoint  Acamadey ', NULL, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Tribeca-Flashpoint-Acamadey-logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Tribeca-Flashpoint-Acamadey-back-ground-1.jpg', 'USA', 'Chicago, Illinois, US', NULL, 'INTERNATIONAL STUDENTS\nIn addition to the criteria listed above, international students are asked to:\n‚Ä¢ Provide an evaluation of high school and/or college transcripts from NACES (National Association of Credential Evaluation Services) or other accredited evaluation company which demonstrates equivalency of high school graduation with a GPA of 2.0 out of 4.0.\n‚Ä¢  Complete one of the following English language proficiency test*: TOEFL (minimum: 80 internet, 550 paper, 213 computer), IELTS (minimum: 6.5), or iTEP (minimum: 4.5).\n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Gradate \n\nBACHELOR''S DEGREE PROGRAMS\nThe Bachelor of Science in Digital Media at Tribeca Flashpoint College is designed to deliver a comprehensive, cross-disciplinary foundation for the many possible paths of a digital media professional.\n‚Ä¢ Bachelor‚Äôs degree programs are 120 credit hours\n‚Ä¢ Each degree program includes a shared groundwork of principles of design, technology and entrepreneurship\n‚Ä¢ Students then select an area of focus in one of three majors: Digital Art, Digital Marketing or Post-Production\n‚Ä¢ Flexible online and on-campus courses are available in all programs\n\nB.S. IN DIGITAL MEDIA, MAJOR IN\n‚Ä¢ DIGITAL ART\n \nB.S. IN DIGITAL MEDIA, MAJOR IN\n‚Ä¢ DIGITAL MARKETING \n\nB.A. IN\n‚Ä¢ POST-PRODUCTION\nB.A. IN\n‚Ä¢ FILM\n B.A. IN\n‚Ä¢ GRAPHIC DESIGN +\nINTERACTIVE MEDIA\nASSOCIATE DEGREE PROGRAMS\nA.A.S. IN\n‚Ä¢ FILM\n A.A.S. IN\n‚Ä¢ RECORDING ARTS\nA.A.S. IN\n‚Ä¢ ANIMATION + VFX\n A.A.S. IN\n‚Ä¢ DESIGN + VISCOM\n A.A.S. IN\n‚Ä¢ DIGITAL MEDIA\n', NULL, '1,600', NULL, NULL, 'Off Campus & on campus ', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', 'TUITION\n\nEstimated Cost of Attendance (Per Semester)\n\nTuition and Fees: $9,957\n\nRoom and Board (if applicable):$4,575\n\nBooks and Supplies: $2,000\n\nPer', '$60 USD ', NULL, 'Spring\nSummer\nFall\n', 'www.tribecaflashpoint.edu/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Tribeca Flashpoint  Acamadey ', 'Founded in 2007 as Flashpoint, The Academy of Media Arts and Sciences, the college entered a 50/50 partnership with Tribeca Enterprises, the company established by Robert De Niro, Jane Rosenthal and Craig Hatkoff best known for producing the Tribeca Film Festival, in April 2010. At the time of the partnership, Flashpoint was renamed Tribeca Flashpoint Media Arts Academy. In 2012, Sterling Capital Partners, a private equity firm, became the majority owner of Tribeca Flashpoint Academy. In April 2015, the school announced that it had become Tribeca Flashpoint College.', 'Founded in 2007 as Flashpoint, The Academy of Media Arts and Sciences, the college entered a 50/50 partnership with Tribeca Enterprises, the company established by Robert De Niro, Jane Rosenthal and Craig Hatkoff best known for producing the Tribeca Film Festival, in April 2010. At the time of the partnership, Flashpoint was renamed Tribeca Flashpoint Media Arts Academy. In 2012, Sterling Capital Partners, a private equity firm, became the majority owner of Tribeca Flashpoint Academy. In April 2015, the school announced that it had become Tribeca Flashpoint College.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(450, 'Trine University', 1884, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Trine-University-logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Trine-University-back-ground-1.jpg', 'USA', NULL, NULL, 'You can apply to Trine without paying any fees. Simply choose the appropriate online application and follow the easy steps listed below.\nMain Campus\nUndergraduate\n-  Application information\nTransfer (daytime Angola campus)\nGraduate\nInternational\nDual Enrollment\nNon Degree\nSummer Non Degree\nSchool of Professional Studies (Adults)\nAdult Undergraduate, Graduate and International\nPeoria, Arizona Campus\nPeoria Undergraduate, Graduate and Dual Enrollment\n', 'Private University [Non-Profit]', '$10,000', 'Undergraduate Programs\nWe offer Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) and Bachelor of Science (B.S.) programs in a broad range of fields including business, education, engineering, health science, and arts and sciences.\n\nGraduate Programs\nWe offer a Master of Science in Engineering Management, a Master of Science with a major in criminal justice, a Master of Science in Leadership, a Master of Business Administration and a Master of Science in Physician Assistant Studies (expected to begin in 2017). We also offer a Doctor of Physical Therapy. \n\nAdult Students\nFor working adults, choose a degree program that best fits your career or life goals in business, engineering, technology, and the humanities.\n\nAdditional Programs\nTrine offers additional programs to enhance your academic experience. Choose from programs for Honors, Study Abroad, co-ops, internships, and more\n\n\n\n\nThree-Year Degree Path\nFor students who are focused and know exactly the professional future they want, we offer the Full Throttlepathway to degree completion. You''ll be positioned to pursue and earn your degree in just three years, through a combination of face-to-face and online courses.\n\nCommunity Education\nIntellectually stimulating, personal enrichment courses for children and adults will help enhance knowledge and skills, and expand horizons into new areas of personal or career interest.\n', 'Earl D. Brooks II, Ph.D', '1700', NULL, NULL, 'Off Campus & on campus ', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', 'Undergraduate Main Campus Students\nSummer 2016 Costs\nTuition - $380/credit hour\nEngineering tuition - $480/credit hour\nFall 2016/Spring 2017 Annual Co', '$60 USD ', NULL, 'Spring\nSummer\nFall\n', 'www.trine.edu', 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=23&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwic7LDenYTPAhVJOo8KHX2CCnMQoiQIogEwFg&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FTrineUniversity%2F&usg=AFQjCNFeCkfOl8vAvIyH1iJ48x98giINDw', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Trine University', 'Trine University, formerly known as Tri-State University, is a private non-profit post-secondary institution located in Angola, Indiana. The school was founded in 1884, and offers degrees in the arts and sciences, business, education and engineering. Trine University is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission and is a member of the North Central Association of Colleges and Schools. It operates several satellite campuses across northern and central Indiana.\nTrine was founded in 1884 as Tri-State Normal College, and retained the reference to the "Tri-State" area for more than 120 years ‚Äî so named because of the school''s location in Indiana and its proximity to Michigan and Ohio. In 1906 the school was renamed Tri-State College, and again in 1975 as Tri-State University. In 2008, the school''s name was changed to the current Trine University, in honor of alumnus Dr. Ralph Trine. The dropping of the "Tri-State" identifier reflected a desire to brand the school as a nationally competitive private university, not to be confused as being state-funded, or as being associated with businesses or organizations nationwide also using the prevalent "Tri-State" tag. Throughout the 1990s, the university opened several satellite campuses in locations throughout northern and central Indiana\n', 'Trine University, formerly known as Tri-State University, is a private non-profit post-secondary institution located in Angola, Indiana. The school was founded in 1884, and offers degrees in the arts and sciences, business, education and engineering. Trine University is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission and is a member of the North Central Association of Colleges and Schools. It operates several satellite campuses across northern and central Indiana.\nTrine was founded in 1884 as Tri-State Normal College, and retained the reference to the "Tri-State" area for more than 120 years ‚Äî so named because of the school''s location in Indiana and its proximity to Michigan and Ohio. In 1906 the school was renamed Tri-State College, and again in 1975 as Tri-State University. In 2008, the school''s name was changed to the current Trine University, in honor of alumnus Dr. Ralph Trine. The dropping of the "Tri-State" identifier reflected a desire to brand the school as a nationally competitive private university, not to be confused as being state-funded, or as being associated with businesses or organizations nationwide also using the prevalent "Tri-State" tag. Throughout the 1990s, the university opened several satellite campuses in locations throughout northern and central Indiana\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
