(486, 'UNIVERSITY OF THE SCIENCES', 1821, 'USA', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/uscienceslogo2.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/usciences.jpg', ' Philadelphia, PA , United States', ' 600 S 43rd St, Philadelphia, PA 19104, United States', NULL, 'Required Documents:\n- Official Transcripts - All Previous Universities\n- TOEFL (90) or IELTS (6.5) - Official Scores Only\n-  (2) Letters of Recommendation\n- Statement of Purpose \n- Copy of Passport\n- Bank Statement \n- USciences Certificate of Finances Form\n- Affidavit of Support\n- NACES evaluation Required\n- GRE Required for: (Minimum 50th percentile)\nBiochemistry\nBiological Sciences\nBiotechnology\nCancer Biology\nChemistry\nHealth Policy\nHealth Psychology\n\n', 'Private', '$10,000', 'Chemistry\nOccupational TherapyBiochemistry\nBiological Sciences\nChemistry\nHealth Policy and Management\nMBA\nOccupational Therapy\n', ' Kathleen Mayes (Interim)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 215-596-8800', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.usciences.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/USciences/', 'https://twitter.com/usciences', 'https://plus.google.com/107041473711373476927', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/23273?trk=tyah', 'https://www.instagram.com/usciences/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/usciences', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/usciences', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'UNIVERSITY OF THE SCIENCES', 'Founded in 1821, The University of the Sciences "USciences" is a university devoted to science and healthcare in the city of Philadelphia. A university focused largely on the sciences, USciences prides itself on its top-notch facilities and its dedicated faculty members, many of whom are top researchers and practitioners in their fields. With over 30 degree programs offered, USciences boasts a 95% employment or advanced degree acceptance rate upon graduation.', 'After its conception in 1821, the college began to grow in enrollment, curriculum, and stature. Although matriculation was originally limited to men, the college became coeducational in 1876. The college initially emphasized the biological and chemical sciences as mainstays of the curriculum in pharmacy but later instituted separate curricula in three other areas: bacteriology, biology, and chemistry.\n\nIn 1921, the name of the institution was changed to Philadelphia College of Pharmacy and Science, with state authorization to grant not only the baccalaureate degree, but also the master‚Äôs and doctorate in all four disciplines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
