agement  ‚Ä¢  \nUrban Affairs- Urban Management  ‚Ä¢  \nUrban Affairs- Urban Planning  ‚Ä¢  \nWomens Studies', ' David R. Hopkins', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 937-775-3333', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, '$50', NULL, 'Spring / Summer / Fall', 'http://www.wright.edu/', 'https://www.facebook.com/WrightStateUniversity', 'https://twitter.com/WrightState', 'https://plus.google.com/117952809397074502841', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wright-state-university', 'https://www.instagram.com/wrightstateu/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/WrightStateU', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/WrightStateU', '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'WRIGHT STATE UNIVERSITY', 'All on-line Applications require the special CollegeStudyUS code of: ICA entered on the application.\n\nWright State University is a large diverse and poular university for International students. They are dedicated to teaching, research, and service in Dayton, Ohio. Wright State''s link to area business, community, and research organizations in and around Dayton offers unique educational opportunities to a diverse student body.\n\nPopular Bachelor and Masters degrees include- Engineering and Business. \nThe student population is made up from international students from over 70 countries.\n\nThe university serves nearly 20,000 students with programs leading to more than 100 undergraduate and 40 Graduate and professional degree programs. Wright State offers innovative educational programs, including Ph.D programs in biomedical sciences, human factors and industrial/organizational psychology, medicine, and professional psychology; the US''s only aerospace medicine residency program. Wright State''s theatre, accounting, chemistry, geology, and engineering programs are recognized for excellence.\n', 'Wright State University''s faculty is dedicated not only to advanced teaching. Most classes are small and taught by faculty where 80% hold the most advanced degrees in their fields. In addition, students gain hands-on experience through a variety of community-based programs, cooperative education, internships, and research projects operated with industry and government.\n\nThe university and the metropolitan area feature a wide variety of cultural opportunities, such as symphonies, opera, ballet, theatre productions, museums, and art galleries. At the undergraduate level, all the engineering major programs are professionally accredited by the Accreditation Board of Engineering and Technology (A.B.E.T.). The Bachelor of Science in Computer Science is accredited by Computer Science Accreditation Board (C.S.A.B.).\n\nAt the Graduate level, all M.B.A. programs are accredited by the A.A.C.S.B. This is the highest accreditation that can be received by a school of Business.\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
